text:
this is the extent of air pollution in a single moment from a single power station. we tend to pollute things: our skies, our seas, our senses. but when the damage is done, how do we depollute? how do we see though the smog and decontaminate ourselves of our negative thoughts, hopelessness and broken will? how do we purify our very psychological being in order to regain courage, drive and joy? why should we, if our minds are bound to become polluted again? i’m reaching out; who can help me answer these questions? ~copingdiary ~
~
~
~

text:
if when you set a goal and you reach the goal, you feel accomplished, please stop reading...this post is not for you.

this post is for the person that wants one fuggin more!

one more rep.
one more dollar.
one more kiss.
one more dance.
one more hug.
one more award.
one more of every fuggin thing.

this post is not for the champion...this post is for the fuggin master.

i didnt realize i used to live broke thru my early 20's thru my early 30's.

settling for less in every fuggin way. if the goal was 10 bucks, 8 bucks was enough. if the goal was a 100%  90% was enough. i would celebrate enough...instead of pushing past my threshold to hit one fuggin more!!! i would stop short because i knew i was ahead of everyone else. i was fine with winning the race even though i knew i could do fuggin better. again, double mcfugg that with a large coke! 
i would basically settle for less than my best...well you know what settling does? it makes you like that jerk christopher columbus when he landed in the carribean...a settler!!!this jerk thought he was going to india, landed in america and called it the west indies...if that ain't settling...i dont know what is. fugg that.

if you want more in your life you need to push for one more. you need to jump of the damn cliff...you need to be fuggin challenged!!! you gotta jump towards your goals on the count of 3, here are your options:

you can jump on 1
get pushed on 2
or let life push youon 3

what's the troof?

most people say they have a dream (jump on 1) but they're too afraid to move. so they wait until "they're ready" basically jump on 1...becomes jump on 3 years later.

they say "imma jump right on 1"...then a year goes by, "immma jump on 1" yeah right!

now if you dont jump on 1, you can get pushed (challenged) on 2. who is gonna push you??? someone that you trust to challenge you to reach your ultimate destination. someone you know can get you there faster than you would...(i.e. the firestarter)

if you dont jump on 1, or get pushed on 2, life will choose for you on 3. most people die on 3. they wait till it's too late. point: jump muthafuggin now

dm me asap for a challenge! 
#firestarterout
#fuego
#howtobeafirestarter

text: haven’t walked away, just too much going on to post! 😊 and, if you’ll notice i have something in common with this tiger whose strategic white patches on the back of his ears must serve well to give the appearance of eyes in the back of his head...but, the difference is, as a mom, i actually must have eyes in the back of my head to catch all the fun going on! much love to other moms out there too! 😄 on a serious note, i have to reassess, not online interests, but, once again how to get my biz going to overcome the financial wake left by the ex as y’all know by now! hard place to be to constantly be sabotaged by someone’s inability to live and let live...and that is what forced me on the journey where i came to value everything and fully realize that life, as i see it, has truly been music in my eyes...so out of the pressure to overcome a whacko has burst forth this dam and desire to create...and yet, the caveat is overcoming the financial dynamic to realize this newfound and forging path to shine a light upon the road ahead...for us and others who may need that light to lead the way out of darkness. so, my prayer is his will be done truly in earth as it is in heaven for our life! thanks for praying too! love everyone’s talent, heart and support here... ❤️🙏😊 #fashionfotog #fashiontees #fashionfotogevita #evita #fashionfotoge #marina #sunset #faith #timesup #fashionphotographer #cooltees #fineartphotographer #clothes #travelwriter #travelphotographer #autismspeaks #tees #tshirts #mugs #hats #purses #designs #tiger #tigerstripes #artdirector #copywriter #metoo #style #copywriter

text: hej och välkommen till en ny vecka i en tid där kvinnors kroppar fortfarande kränks systematiskt! i veckan som gått har en kvinnokropp hittats död, bunden i en väska. våldtäkter har anmälts. kvinnors egna bilder har hängts ut på porrsajter och dockor utklädda till kvinnokroppar med målet att uppföra sig som en perfekt kvinna (alltså ligga helt jävla passiv med brösten stående rakt ut, benen isär och levereras i trosa och litet linne) säljs till män. och så en man som med munskydd(!) far runt och greppar tag i kvinnors rumpor och gör det president trump tycker är helt naturligt: greppar tag i kvinnors fittor. tio anmälningar hittills. och ännu en man har fått mängder av kvinnor att känna oro eller rädsla för att inte få ha sin kropp ifred. det ska tydligen vara helt jävla omöjligt att kunna få vara fredad från sexuella övergrepp. och till er som undrar varför jag inte skriver om ”mord på män”. därför att 1. det gör så många andra. media till exempel. 2. mord på män där de hamnar bundna i en väska brukar kunna kopplas till grovt kriminella gäng och drabbar således inte en random man och 3. därför att den typen av mord inte gör resten av männen rädda för sina liv och kroppar och 4. därför att det handlar om kvinnohat. vilket inte är kopplat till mäns mord på män generellt sätt.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
my good friend aaron helped me make this video where i speak about my childhood sexual abuse, the effects it had on my development as a child & teenager & how i have coped vs how i am coping now. i also speak to the benefits of seeking counseling, offer supportive words to other survivors and give information for @calgarycasa which offers (free) counseling to survivors of sexual abuse. they have helped me over the past 12 years until i finally built up the courage to do the right thing (for me) and report my abuse. i have hated this last year and a half of going through the police investigation and the court process but we are closing in on sentencing date and for me this is the light at the end of what has been a very dark tunnel for a very long time. 
thank you to my amazing friend @lee.k.tan for helping me to edit this into the masterpiece it has become. i unfortunately am unable to share the video until after court is finished but i can assure you it is powerful, emotional and inspiring all at once. here's to hoping i can share it with the world sooner than later. 
#ccasa #roadtorecovery #helpingothershelpsyourself #metoo #reportabuse #stopthecycleofabuse

text:
i got flowers today. it wasn't my birthday or any other special day. we had our first argument last night. he said a lot of cruel things that really hurt me. i know he was sorry and didn't mean the things he said. because i got flowers today. 
i got flowers today. it wasn't our anniversary or any other special day. last night, he threw me into a wall and started to choke me. it seemed like a nightmare. i couldn't believe it was real. i woke up this morning sore and bruised all over. i know he must be sorry because he sent me flowers today. 
i got flowers today. it wasn't mother's day or any other special day. last night, he beat me up again. and it was much worse than all other times. if i leave him, what will i do? how will i take care of my kids? what about money? i' m afraid of him and scared to leave. but i know he must be sorry because he sent me flowers today. 
i got flowers today. today was a very special day. it was the day of my funeral. last night he finally killed me. he beat me to death. 
if only i had gathered enough courage and strength to leave him, i would not have gotten flowers today. 
this poem is dedicated to all the victims and survivors of domestic violence. 
you ask, why didn't she leave?

i ask, why did he hit?
#metoo #domesticviolence #domesticabuse #speakout #hebroughtmeflowers #pain #hehitme #itsnevertoolate #nomore #futureswithoutviolence #poems #abusepoem #support #supportwomen #women #equality #leavehim #survivor

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: “we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.” documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takers’ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebook’s “platform policy” allowed only collection of friends’ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebook’s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate “information warfare” against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

🎬
film review
🎬
widows
🎬
⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️/5
🎬
“because no one thinks we have the balls to pull this off.”
🎬
when a heist goes wrong, three women are left widowed by their criminal husbands and left with huge debts from their illegal activities. after discovering the plans for the men’s next heist, the women begin to form a plan of their own...
🎬
widows is directed by steve mcqueen and is inspired by the lynda la plante novel. the film features a fantastic cast that includes viola davis, michelle rodriguez, elizabeth debicki, colin farrell, robert duvall and black panther’s daniel kaluuya as a truly terrifying villain. with a strong female led cast, this is a heist movie with a difference and is gritty and realistic in its portrayal of a heist compared to other films. set in chicago, the film acts as a social commentary on america, particularly in terms of class and race. 12 years a slave director mcqueen subtly offers a hint of issues such as black lives matter, weaving these elements intricately into the storyline. the film also tackles issues of domestic abuse, grief and corruption.
🎬
widows is a thrilling heist movie, aided by a sharp script from gillian flynn and mcqueen and a tense score by hans zimmer. the film also has some tender moments, with much comedic light relief interspersed into the story, particularly in the form of elizabeth debicki. widows is an intelligent crime drama that proves women can take centre stage, no matter the genre. the film feels timely and relevant in this new era of #metoo and #timesup, with a diverse female cast at the forefront of the film as their characters take control of their lives and prove to be formidable and powerful people.
🎬
have you seen widows or read the book? do you have a favourite female led film or book?
🎬

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text_retweet:
it’s hard to get a good birth in the hospital these days! it’s possible, and easier with some staff than others, but you get who you get when it’s a small town and there’s no other ob nurse. 😬
.
going in prepared may not be enough! .
the only way i’d ever birth in a hospital again is literally if i’m unconscious and to be cut open! 
but. if for some weird reason, i’d ever birth in a hospital again, i’d never go in alone, without the professional support of a doula! .
when you’re in labor land, you need someone who’s knowledgeable about birth, not emotionally attached, and on your side. a doula fits this description. .
dm to book a complimentary interview with me, and we’ll discuss how a doula can benefit you, on a personal level! .
#doulalove #youareincharge #haveanextraordinarybirth #yourbirthyourpoweryoureextraordinary #doula #nebraska #centralnebraska .
.
#repost @birthmonopoly with @get_repost
・・・
normalizing disrespect through jokes about birth plans is just one part of a culture where birthing people are disrespected in more explicit and serious ways. 📣
it's meaningful that this model comes from one originally created about rape culture. birth is where misogyny and inherent power dynamics meet over women's bodies--it just happens to be in a medical setting.
📣
what can we do about this? get on the waitlist for my #knowyourrights course coming out this week--packed with info to empower you and your clients about your rights in birth! waitlist: www.birthmonopoly.com/birth-rights
📣
[concept from and thanks to11thprincipleconsent.org/ consent-propaganda/rape-culture-pyramid"]
📣

text:
trauma has a silver lining;
trauma's happen, big t or little t, they change us. the damage gets done. but you can be bitter or better. choose better please, broken people break others, unintentionally but by choosing to ignore or downplay your trauma, your feelings, you spread the pain around. when you actively choose to. face your trauma big or small, you show the greatest bravery and the strongest heart!
when you face your trauma every terrified step forward is bravery!
when you face your trauma your bs tolorance goes way down! your authenticity raises! you can't  allow other people drama to cloud your progress and that's ok! those who can't deal with the reality of your trauma are a) lucky enough to have no personal experience hence no empathy, b) not able to. and that's ok too! not everyone can! or c) couldn't care less or think you deserve it, those people are assholes so be greatful they've shown you their truth and act accordingly.
trauma will teach you what is worth your energy and what makes up fakery in your life, its cleansing. and healing from trauma might be hard work but it feels like victory with every battle won! #nfiniteheart #trauma #ptsd #ptss #cptsd #cptssrecovery #chronicillness #terminalillness #healing #palliativecare #love #caring #counselling #lifecoach #metoo #youvegotthis #consulting

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text_retweet: why are people passive to this? these are babies. living creatures not products.  reposted from @antonyle55 -  via @earthlove777 rp @erinrileycarrasco i didn’t become vegan because i didn’t like the way meat and dairy tasted. i became vegan because i hated the taste of cruelty and suffering. so many people don’t know this, so here’s the truth: all calves born in the dairy industry are “bi-products.” all dairy cows need to be pregnant to produce milk. they don’t just produce milk on their own. farmers then steal the milk meant for the calves and sell to humans to drink. most calves are taken from their mother within the first 24 hours and either slaughtered or if a boy, sent to veal sheds where they are isolated in a tiny shed for apprx 5 months and then slaughtered. female calves may be spared, but are destined to live the same life as their mother and between 4-5 yrs of age, are also slaughtered after a life of being confined, put on the rape rack and having their babies stolen over and over. their bodies are spent after years of milk ”production” and then their flesh is sold to meat eaters. in the wild, cows live upwards of 20 years. you’re not going to hear about this on mainstream media. why do you think that is? that’s the truth. that’s dairy and that is cruelty. just because you like the taste of cheese does not negate the fact that this is what you’re paying for. #februdairy #dairyfree #dairy #govegan #crueltyfree #meat #hamburger #burger #pizzahut #pizzapizza #ilovepizza #cheesecake #cheesecakefactory #cheesey #vegetarian #creamy #cream #creamcheese #dairyisscary #stopseparatingfamilies #burgerking #veggies #farmher #vegano #metoo #seperation #donttakeourplanetforgranted - #regrann

text:
“any girl hiding behind a mask,

first of all, i understand.

i understand the pain you feel everyday. i understand your fear of admitting how you really feel. i understand how hard it is to wake up and wish you could curl up in a ball and not deal with the world. i understand what it's like to feel alone, despite being surrounded by people who love you. i understand not feeling loved and hating yourself for feeling that way. and most importantly, i understand using a smile so people don't see how you feel.” * i have been that girl for years, i have been the girl who makes jokes, who laughs out loud but cries inside, that makes fun of herself rather then facing the demons of her past but a few months ago i made the decision to face the “girl behind the mask”. this has been one of the biggest struggles and triumphs in my life, but with love and encouragement, i will some day 100% love that girl. #motivationmonday #nevergiveup #metoo

en el camino de lograr con éxito nuestro proyecto de vida resultan fundamentales, sea éste cuál sea, seguir ciertas recomendaciones importantes: 1)un cuaderno de anotaciones o diario donde tomemos nota de ideas, sueños, iluminaciones y vislumbramientos que vayamos concibiendo en el trayecto que vamos desarrollando junto a nuestra pareja,familia,socios o equipo,según cada caso.2) constante interacción con nuestros aliados para avanzar y facilitar el progreso del proyecto.3)monitoreo de debilidades,amenazas,fortalezas y oportunidades.4) celebración compartida de logros y avances.
antes de avanzar, un aspecto a considerar es lo relativo a soltar la necesidad de control .
aunque cueste superar barreras y esquemas, tod@s tenemos derecho a ser felices y a estar más allá de todo lo que el locus de control externo quiera imponernos. cada uno tiene suficiente con centrarse en su propósito de vida y para descubrirlo sólo necesitamos conectar con dios todopoderoso, que habita dentro de cada uno e ilumina nuestro camino.
sin recriminar, sin discriminar, sin incriminar ...simplemente viviendo y dejando vivir.
reconozcamos y confiemos en el poder de dios.
actuemos siempre pensando si en verdad nuestras acciones, pensamientos,palabras y decisiones están colaborando para permitir que dios opere en nuestras vidas:
co- operando! 
vivamos #creandobienestar !

link in bio to hear why the term ‘toxic masculinity’ is so polarizing, and what gillette was hoping to achieve with their latest campaign ⬆️🎧

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
let’s talk about slut shaming.

actually, let’s talk body-shaming, assumptions, and how some people just suck.

a few local, suburban moms (like all their names should just be jan... sorry to any rad women out their named jan 😂) were on a facebook tirade about how slutty the women at the grammy’s were dressed. one woman was so ballsy so as to make reference to the #metoo movement and called women hypocrites.

listen here, jan 🙄 women are allowed to wear whatever they want, however they want, and you are no better or worse than them even if your cotton turtleneck is pulled up to your chins with your crocks on. in fact, if that’s how you feel the most empowered, then rock it loud and proud. i’m going to be the last person who judges you based on what you wear. what i will judge you on, though, is your character.

a woman’s outfit is not an invitation for sex. nor is it an invitation for you to project your assumptions. in fact, in the world we live in now, those types of judgements from one woman to another is just one small part of the whole problem.

i don’t watch things like the grammys, i have no idea who was there or what anyone wore or didn’t wear. i literally don’t even care. but what i do know is this:

there needs to be unity among women. with a universal understanding that we can show up fully expressed without having to worry about being called a slut, or assuming we’re dumb, or desperate, or “asking to be raped.” i have been incredibly fortunate to never have been a victim of assault of any kind. but it’s not because of what i wear or don’t wear.

but can you imagine having to worry about other women judging your motives based on what you wear? i can’t speak for men. but i can speak to women: do better.

please, judge me based on the words that come out of my mouth and the actions that comprise how i live my life.

but don’t judge me, or any woman, based on what she decides to wear.

go ahead, jan 🙄 clutch your pearls in horror of the “slutty” girl who doesn’t wear pants on instagram. i’ll inspire your daughters some day to become fearless enough to stand up to women like you in defense of women everywhere. you’re 👏🏽the👏🏽worst👏🏽
name: Strength + Anti-Diet Coach

text:
lean in really close and listen to me... “i don’t care what they say.  it’s still not your fault.”
🙅🏼‍♀️
the first few times i shared my story with others about my attack, they unintentionally asked questions that packed on more shame than i was already carrying.
😞
“what were you wearing?”, “how much did you drink?”, “did you tell anyone?”
it’s still not your fault... even if they ask those questions.
💔
cause here’s the thing: i don’t care if you went walking down main street buck naked at 2am drunk as a skunk... that’s not a consent to touch you.
🖤
would that action have a negative consequence?  probably.  unfortunately,  we live in a fallen world full of people ready to take advantage instead of lend a helping hand.
✋🏼 but- it’s still not your fault.
🖤
people don’t understand how their questions can dig daggers into an already shame infested wound... but i’m here to tell you... it’s still not your fault.
🖤
i don’t care how much you drank, what you wore, what you said, how late you were out, or even whether you could muster the strength to fight...
it’s still not your fault.
❤️
if you’ve been hurt by someone and the wound is still fresh, still bleeding, still weighing you down with lies, shame, fears, and darkness... let me be a voice in that lonely place whispering- it’s still not your fault.
❤️
@rainn is a resource for you, @journeytohealministries is another, and so am i.
🖤
if i were standing in front of you right now i’d lean over, grab your hand, and tell you it’s still not your fault. ✨
if you’re struggling right now or know someone who is, don’t ask questions, sit in the ashes of their pain and be a listening ear.
🌟
let them know they are loved and there is help when they are ready to receive it.
#itsstillnotyourfault #metoo #shespeaks #shespeakstruth #unashamed #sexualassault #sexualassaultsurvivor

-
❌if you are forced into an act by violence or the threat of violence to yourself, to a loved one or to your property.
-
❌if you are drunk, drugged, asleep or unconscious. this means that if you’ve been drinking heavily or taking drugs, you are not able to consent to sex.
-
❌if you are younger then 12 years old or mentally challenged.
-
❌if you are forced into consent by your boss or your teacher, for example if you are led to think that refusing sex will affect your position at work or at your learning institute.
-
❌if a professional or someone in authority has deceived you and made you believe that you need to submit to a sexual act for your physical, emotional or spiritual health.

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
my heart is broken, but still somehow full.  thank you stephanie for sharing your story, and for being a voice for all the other women carrying different versions of the same story hidden deep in their hearts.  people wonder why women don't come forward when they get assaulted, but the answer is right here. women almost never get justice, and they are left to find their own path to healing. it's never an easy road, but we all stand together in our collective trauma, because sometimes it's the only thing we can do.
.
.
.
#amightyforce #metoo #neverthelessshepersisted

text:
“what if you can’t fight him off because he is bigger than you?”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
a fire lit inside me. it was unlike anything i had ever felt before. words began to fly out of my mouth, “you look at me. every single one of you, look straight into my eyes. you are worth fighting for. you fight for your life!”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
although i didn’t realize it until hours later that evening, as i processed the events of the day, that moment changed my life forever.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last july, i had the opportunity to help lead a group of high school students from our church on a mission trip to kenya. we were working with schools in a village there, and from the moment we met these amazing people, they showered us with love and acceptance, unlike anything i've ever experienced before. during our 30 minute bus ride from our hotel to the village on our last day at the schools, we were informed that we needed to lead talks about puberty to the older students, separated by gender.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
as we entered into the room full of 7th and 8th grade girls, i looked around at the bare walls of the classroom and asked god to give me the words to say to these girls.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i started off talking about periods and cramps, but then one of the teachers brought up the subject of guys taking advantage of girls. they asked what to do in a situation like that. in the moment, god gave me 4 things for these girls to do. say no, fight them off, run away and then tell someone.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that was when one question changed the direction of my life.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this has become my anthem. fight for your life. i wonder how many #metoo moments could have been avoided if the female knew she had the option to fight? the first instinct is to freeze. we must change that.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
we must also change our instinct to accept things as they are and fall victim to our lives. aside from death, illness or trying to control someone else, you have the power to change whatever is going wrong in your life.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
continued in comments 👇🏻
(hat and pullover by @jordansgems 😍)

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
a fire lit inside me. it was unlike anything i had ever felt before. words began to fly out of my mouth, “you look at me. every single one of you, look straight into my eyes. you are woh fighting for. you fight for your life!”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
although i didn’t realize it until hours later that evening, as i processed the events of the day, that moment changed my life forever.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last july, i had the oppounity to help lead a group of high school students from our church on a mission trip to kenya. we were working with schools in a village there, and from the moment we met these amazing people, they showered us with love and acceptance, unlike anything i have ever experienced before. during our 30 minute bus ride from our hotel to the village on our last day at the schools, we were informed that we needed to lead talks about pubey to the older students, separated by gender.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
as we entered into the room full of 7th and 8th grade girls, i looked around at the bare walls of the classroom and asked god to give me the words to say to these girls.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i staed off talking about periods and cramps, but then one of the teachers brought up the subject of guys taking advantage of girls. they asked what to do in a situation like that. in the moment, god gave me 4 things for these girls to do. say no, fight them off, run away and then tell someone.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that was when one question changed the direction of my life.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this has become my anthem. fight for your life. i wonder how many  moments could have been avoided if the female knew she had the option to fight? the first instinct is to freeze. we must change that.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
we must also change our instinct to accept things as they are and fall victim to our lives. aside from death, illness or trying to control someone else, you have the power to change whatever is going wrong in your life.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
continued in comments 👇🏻
(hat and pullover by  😍)

text:
in 2006, tarana burke began using the phrase “me too” to raise awareness of the pervasiveness of sexual abuse and assault in society. in 2017 the movement became viral with the hashtag #metoo and propelled numerous survivors of sexual abuse and assault to come forward with their stories. tarana has been involved in activism since her time in college at auburn university, where she organized press conferences and protests regarding economic and racial justice. she has also been involved and founded organizations that seek to empower young women of color.
thank you, tarana, for speaking up and sharing your story and from that, inspiring thousands of survivors to say me too.

text:
jade jackman
*
we spoke with director jade jackman, newly added to the free the bid database of directors, about her latest work "the future is fluid," created in partnership with #irregularlabs and gucci x chime for change.
*
jade is a 25 year old filmmaker, currently represented by black dog films in the uk. she has worked with platforms such as boiler room, nowness, i-d, vice and the guardian.
*
"this film was made in partnership with #irregularlabs for the re-launch of gucci’s foundation, chime for change. in my signature style, the film blurs the boundary between fact and fiction, while exploring gen-z’s hopes and dreams for gender around the world.
*
this is a way of working that i adopted while shooting, 'calling home,' an experimental documentary that amplifies the voices of young women held in immigration and removal / detention facilities. by borrowing techniques from music videos, fashion films or interesting brand collaborations, i believe that we can engage new audiences and change-up outdated or marginalizing representations.
*
i am committing myself this year to collaborate with a more diverse range of crew and seek out new talent, too. free the bid’s mission in part inspired my all femaleand gnc crew for my latest project, 'station'. in the wake of #metoo, the documentary hybrid takes place in the moment that a woman decides not to report an incident of sexual assault to the police. as survivors and women, we are taking back control of the narrative of sexual violence and, for our contributors, they have said it is empowering to share this with us too."
*
visit freethebid.com to view jade’s profile and discover the work of many other talented women directors!
*
follow jade on instagram: @jadeshamraeff
*

text: fear in our body: "by the time we reach adulthood we have difficulty recognizing the sensation of fear in our bodies, not because it is not there, but because it is the foundation for a life-long development of what i call emotional survival adaptations that turn cognitive and behavioral over the course of our developmental years. fear develops often before we are able to remember, or speak—therefore we are unable to put words or cognition to the experience. it is 100% visceral and triggered by sensory input from either outside or inside of our bodies. but as we develop we respond to these triggers in ways that are appropriate for the development of our brains, and later our minds.  by the time we are entering toddlerhood we are capable of understanding basic “cause and effect” principle.  much like after a near miss a gazelle will remember where the vulnerable (re dangerous) areas of the plains are, we also can conceptualize how to avoid danger. but in the case of humans, our sense of danger (or a risk to survival) often remains relegated to our perception of disconnection. and when we are very young we can’t conceptualize this danger outside of something we did. the mind of a child is not capable of seeing outside of the self to the parent or caregiver, which is to say that if we spill a glass of milk and the person we are depending on for connection (re survival) becomes angry and loses their temper we are not capable of considering that perhaps they just had a bad day at work and are over-reacting. when we are children, our bodies and minds register a risk of disconnection as caused by something we said or did, and in response we adapt." #trauma #healing #yoga #bodyawareness #mindfulness #community #books #womenempowerment #metoo

*
this is a way of working that i adopted while shooting, 'calling home,' an experimental documentary that amplifies the voices of young women held in immigration and removal / detention facilities. by borrowing techniques from music videos, fashion films or interesting brand collaborations, i believe that we can engage new audiences and change-up outdated or marginalizing representations.
*

text:
according to the national sexual violence resource center * 1 in 5 women and 1 in 71 men will be raped at some point in their lives.
* in the united stares 1 in 3 women and 1 in 6 men experienced some form of contact sexual violence in their lifetime.
* 51.1% of female victims of rape reported being raped by an intimate partner and 40.8% by an acquaintance.
* 52.4% of male victims report being raped by an acquaintance and 15.1% by a stranger.
* 49.5% of multiracial women and over 45% of american indian/alaska native women were subjected to some form of contact sexual violence in their lifetime.
* 91% of victims of rape and sexual assault are female, and 9% are male * in 8 out of 10 cases of rape, the victim knew the perpetrator.
* 8% of rapes occur while the victim is at work. 
the problem of sexual violence runs rampant, and yet rape is the most under-reported crime; 63% of sexual assaults are not reported to police. of the remaining 37% that are reported less than 10% are instances of false reporting. the facts are clear, and still the culture that would rather victims of sexually based crimes remain silent prevails. 
join rebecca macceile as she throws off the shackles of silence and raises her voice. turquoise boot straps: a survivor’s thoughts provides a glimpse into her journey of self discovery while tackling many controversial topics at the height of the metoo era. 
#comingsoon #writingcommunity #newbookalert #indieauthorsofinstagram #metoo #ptsdsurvivor #feminism #saam #nsvrc

text: today i finally say #metoo today after almost 4 years i had the privilege of looking my offender in the face, speak my raw and explicit truth and be the sole reason he was locked away. today i have felt fear, anger, sadness, but also relief, and pride. i took a stand and although it took years for this outcome, i can rest easy knowing that all my hard work has been paid off and that he will never forget what he did to me. for those wondering, no this is not for appraisal, this is to show any other females that it is okay to be vulnerable. it is okay to stand up for yourself. know your worth and know that your voice can be heard, if you are willing to speak up. it’ll be worth it my love ❤️. this life is a constant battle, and if you have experienced a sexual harm done to you, i know how you feel. no words can describe the relief i feel in getting justice, a true smile on my face knowing i fought for myself and other women. anyone struggling with something similar feel free to get in touch with me. #speakyourtruth #birdsetfree #fightforyourself

text:
"collective action and shared responsibility for driving gender parity is what makes international women's day successful"

did you know?
"international women's day (march 😎 is a global day celebrating the social, economic, cultural and political achievements of women. the day also marks a call to action for accelerating gender parity. international women's day (iwd) has occurred for well over a century, with the first march 8 iwd gathering supported by over a million people in austria, denmark, germany and switzerland. prior to this the socialist party of america, united kingdom's suffragists and suffragettes, and further groups campaigned for women equality. today, iwd belongs to all groups collectively everywhere. iwd is not country, group or organisation specific. make iwd your day! - everyday!

how are will you be celebrating international women's day this year? get involved and/or join us:

i'm excited to speaking at the #internationalwomensday hosted by #womeninhealthcareuk in #leeds #weethood this year. #iwd #iwd2018 #pressforprogress #metoo #timesup #womeninbusiness #womenempowerment #womensmarch #beboldforchange

definición de feminismo: el conjunto heterogéneo​ de ideologías y de movimientos políticos, culturales y económicos que tienen como objetivo la igualdad de derechos entre hombres y mujeres.
osea que.. si usted:
-cree en la igualdad de género
-cree que la mujer y el hombre deben de ganar lo mismo por hacer el mismo trabajo
-cree que la mujer debe de gozar de iguales derechos y beneficios que el hombre
-cree que la mujer debe de tener igual rango de oportunidades económicas y laborales que los hombres
(y muchisimas mas)

-las feministas no odiamos a los hombres. esto ni siquiera tiene sentido cuando lo dicen
-ser feminista no quiere decir que una mujer quiera ser hombre
-si usted apoya el machismo, usted no es feminista

peace para todos🌈 📸 @rodxesproductions

text:
it’s my birthday week so i kinda don’t know how to ackkkk. 😝😂 birthdays have always been a huge thing for me. i’m the awkward person that always does a bday countdown and won’t let anyone around me forget that a national holiday is about to arrive! 
though birthdays have been special to me, i’ve also known them to be traumatic. 
5 years ago, as i was getting ready to celebrate my birthday, i was struggling with deep depression after a breakup with my long-time college boyfriend. in the midst of my depression, i was sexually assaulted in the wee hours of the morning of my 23rd birthday.

when something like that happens to you, you don’t know where to begin to pick up the pieces of your life. i spent so much time feeling ashamed, feeling like i had done something to convince this man that i wanted him when i didn't, feeling like i should have been more careful... the list goes on. but god! 🙌🏽 the very thing that should have taken me out was the same thing that god used to draw me closer to him. though i felt so defeated at the beginning of my healing process, i realize that god was so intentional with me and that i was victorious in him. there was nothing too difficult for jesus to heal and restore. 
at that point, i made a decision to recommit my life to god fully and to let his plan lead in my life. i allowed god to heal me and show me that i was not damaged goods because of my experience.

5 years later, and i'm still standing. i'm thriving and transparent about my journey. i am absolutely an overcomer, and my voice will not be silenced!

i share my full story and the healing journey god took me on in my book the morning after prayer. 
i'm celebrating 28 so hard because i really fought hard to get here. depression almost took me out. the trauma almost took me out. but. it. didn't. god had so much more planned in store for me, and it's only the beginning!

this is to 28. and to the authentic smile in this pic because god is just so faithful! #aquarius #birthday #love #jesus #metoo #jesussaves

"i feel cluster fuck news dumps, reg life bullshit and piercing self doubt from new found anxiety & depression after a #cancer loss in 2014 🔧
but i breathe.
inhale my herb...
and remember...i didn't ask to be here!
shit happened to me 5 yrs ago that threw a mother fucking wrench in my shit!!!

i'm finding me.
i'm fucking winging it. like all of us!
this is my story.
i hate being out of work. but i'm still ok being broke. 
i'm rich in knowing i'm still in control of writing my story! 
no one is gonna have their say when i'm gone on what they thought life was for me. i witnessed that first hand.
no one can make you feel what you don't want to feel! 
choices to stay absent when i was a pile of dust is seered in me.
so i sit in my loniness and found myself again. 
the me i knew i could trust. that would never decide over me.
and i know i'm proud to say i'm still learning"-#stonedagegear

text: the situations the  #metoo movement has been exposing has been going on forever in entertainment. wanda, our real life heroine, was probably no exception. in our dramatic musical there are some uncomfortable moments. our hopes as writers is that the audience will feel uncomfortable enough to understand what it is like for a woman to be dehumanized, misogynized, and taken advantage of by a man.  all these years a woman’s voice was unheard, ignored, or she wasn’t able to speak.  some generations just accepted it as something that happens (i know mine did). we (women) justified it and accepted it, even though inside we felt slimy, awkward and fearful in those situations. hoping to shed a little light on this in this musical, not in a political way, but in a human way.  for more info go to savagethemusical.com and stream/download our single “wanda savage”. #performingarts #musicaltheatrelife #theatrelife #actorslife #actor  #hollywood #oldhollywood #silentfilm  #entertainment #musicaltheatre #musical #broadway #broadwayshow #broadwaybound #broadwayshows #broadwayworld #broadwaymusical #newmusical #newmusicalert #womenempowerment #timesup #believewomen #womensreality #believesurvivors #everydaysexism #womenofbroadway #broadwaytheatre

text:
what i’ve chosen through my high conflict divorce and co parenting ... ********************************** more often than not god calls us to do things that just do not make sense in this earthly realm. •
“sometimes faith will make you look stupid, until it starts to rain” - noah 
noah looked insane for building the ark. 
he was talked about and mocked. 
no one understood, 
but god did ! 
and when god called him into action, whether noah was going to look insane or not, he built the ark. 
noah acted on gods call and in his faith, no matter what the people around him were saying. 
i’ve recognized this to be true in my walk through my divorce and co parenting situation. 
god has continued to call me to do things that honestly i can not even understand. . 
to forgive the “unforgivable” 
to love those who continually come against you. 
to seek understanding instead of acting upon anger and hate. 
to stand in peace when there is confusion and conflict. 
i used to ask him why! 
but now i ask him, how can you use me in this

and usually that means, “buckle up amie, set aside yourself and just do what god has asked, not what you feel. “

like noah, i seek to act in faith, even when that means it doesn’t make sense, and i am at risk of peoples judgement. 
i have chosen a daily surrender of my own thoughts and my own feelings and even the thoughts of others to pursue gods understanding and relentless love above all. 
any divorce is not easy, 
let’s get real—— neither is co parenting! 
however, when you can look to the creator of all the universe and know he has your back, 
you can step out of the way and allow god to do his thing. 
so instead of holding onto anger, bitterness, abandonment, and pain 
i choose to pursue 
understanding 
compassion 
peace 
and 
love 
and as i do so, i find my own peace, love and joy in my daily life. 
all it comes down to is a choice. 
so what will you do with it ? •
•
•
•

text:
...
ما الومهم من جماله 💔😂😂😂😂🤣🤣🤣🤣🤣
.
.

تحدث الممثل #ماساكي_سودا في برنامج 'gyoretsu no dekiru horitsu sodanjo' عن تحرش المعجبات به، حيث قال انه كان في الخارج في احد الايام ورصدنه معجبات كبيرات في السن واستمررن بالصراخ وبعدها قاموا بعناقه ولمس وجهه رغما عنه وفكر في تلك اللحظة "إذا كان رجل كبير السن يعانق فتاة صغيرة ، فإنه سيعتبر بالتأكيد تحرشًا جنسيًا ، ومع ذلك ، هل هو جيد إذا كانت مرأة من تفعل هذا؟" ثم قال : اليست جريمة ان يأتي شخص فجأة تأتي ويقوم بمعانقتك؟
.
أجاب المحامي هارو كيتامورا: "إنه في الأساس عمل إجرامي"، وعلق قائلاً: "إنها ليست مشكلة إذا أعطى الشخص موافقته ولكن عندما يفعل الشخص هذا دون موافقة فإنه يصبح هجومًا/تحرشًا".
.
#تعليقات_مستخدمي_الانترنت_اليابانيين
.
1- لماذا السيدات الكبيرات يكونون مجنونات؟ من المؤسف انك ان تستطيع رفضهم بسبب صورتك كفنان
2- الا يقوم الفنانيين باحداث المصافحة لتجنب مثل هذه الحوادث
3- على الفنانيين ان يكونوا اكثر صرامة مع المعجبين هناك حقا أولئك الاوتاكو الحمقى الذين يتصرفون كما لو ان المشهور ملك لهم
4- كنت ساصرخ عليهم على الفور لو قام أحدهم فجأة بعناقي ولمس وجهي
5- لجميع من يقول انه أيضا مخطئ لانه سمح لهم وكان عليه الحديث اذا اوقفهم ستنتهي صورته ستقولون انه متكبر وان عليه شكر المعجبين الذين يجعلوه يكسب المال وتبدؤون بالتمر عليه
6- كانجاني اوكورا تحدث أيضا عن شي مشابه يحدث له
7- أولئك الجدات الجاهلات لو قام رجل فجأة بعناقك ولمسك هل تعتقدون انه امر جيد لكنتم تحدثتم في كل مكان عن مدى قبح الذكور
8- بتأكيد هن من كانساي لذا لايعلمون شي عن التحضر أولئك الجدات القديمات
9- لماذا لو حدث نفس الشي مع ايدول أنثى ستقف معها كل النساء ويطلبون بمعاقبة الرجال بينما لايحدث شي عندما يكون الفنان رجل!!
10- لماذا لاتعبرونه تحرش جنسي اذا قامت المرأة بالتهجم على الرجل هذا أمر شائع ولكن لا أحد يصنفه بهذا الشكل لماذا؟! لنقم نحن الرجال بعمل حركة مشابهة ل #metoo لضمان حقوقنا
.
المصدر:@soby_chan

stop_filter_tweet: ... ما الومهم من جماله 💔😂😂😂😂🤣🤣🤣🤣🤣 . . تحدث الممثل برنامج 'gyoretsu dekiru horitsu sodanjo ' عن تحرش المعجبات به، حيث قال انه كان في الخارج في احد الايام ورصدنه معجبات كبيرات في السن واستمررن بالصراخ وبعدها قاموا بعناقه ولمس وجهه رغما عنه وفكر في تلك اللحظة `` إذا كان رجل كبير السن يعانق فتاة صغيرة ، فإنه سيعتبر بالتأكيد تحرشًا جنسيًا ، ومع ذلك ، هل هو جيد إذا كانت مرأة من تفعل هذا؟ '' ثم قال : اليست جريمة ان يأتي شخص فجأة تأتي ويقوم بمعانقتك؟ . أجاب المحامي هارو كيتامورا : `` إنه في الأساس عمل إجرامي '' ، وعلق قائلاً : `` إنها ليست مشكلة إذا أعطى الشخص موافقته ولكن عندما يفعل الشخص هذا دون موافقة فإنه يصبح هجومًا/تحرشًا '' . . عليقات_مستخدمي_الانترنت_اليابانيين . 1- لماذا السيدات الكبيرات يكونون مجنونات؟ من المؤسف انك ان تستطيع رفضهم بسبب صورتك كفنان 2- الا يقوم الفنانيين باحداث المصافحة لتجنب مثل هذه الحوادث 3- على الفنانيين ان يكونوا اكثر صرامة مع المعجبين هناك حقا أولئك الاوتاكو الحمقى الذين يتصرفون كما لو ان المشهور ملك لهم 4- كنت ساصرخ عليهم على الفور لو قام أحدهم فجأة بعناقي ولمس وجهي 5- لجميع من يقول انه أيضا مخطئ لانه سمح لهم وكان عليه الحديث اذا اوقفهم ستنتهي صورته ستقولون انه متكبر وان عليه شكر المعجبين الذين يجعلوه يكسب المال وتبدؤون بالتمر عليه 6- كانجاني اوكورا تحدث أيضا عن شي مشابه يحدث له 7- أولئك الجدات الجاهلات لو قام رجل فجأة بعناقك ولمسك هل تعتقدون انه امر جيد لكنتم تحدثتم في كل مكان عن مدى قبح الذكور 8- بتأكيد هن من كانساي لذا لايعلمون شي عن التحضر أولئك الجدات القديمات 9- لماذا لو حدث نفس الشي مع ايدول أنثى ستقف معها كل النساء ويطلبون بمعاقبة الرجال بينما لايحدث شي عندما يكون الفنان رجل ! ! 10- لماذا لاتعبرونه تحرش جنسي اذا قامت المرأة بالتهجم على الرجل هذا أمر شائع ولكن لا أحد يصنفه بهذا الشكل لماذا؟ ! لنقم نحن الرجال بعمل حركة مشابهة ل حقوقنا . المصدر :

text:
f*** you medicine was deeply healing for me last year, and it's been necessary for me to revisit it now & then, so i can keep my boundaries strong(er).
.
i sat in sacred space, and let loose my anger, playing over scenes from my past that had tortured my emotions for years. my rage showed me the lessons in them & then i let loose with with screaming mental cries of f*** you to the pain, to those who'd hurt & betrayed me, to myself for being so stupid & for blaming myself. 
over & over, until i found i was repeating my mantra in a gutteral grumbles & was dizzy from how light i felt.
.
then i was silent and free.

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

#marketing #trending #profit #political #success #collective #ootd #politics #trending #metoo #timesup #trend #strategy #feminism #elections #freedom #graphics #future #lifestyle #journalist #journalism #luxury #luxurylife  #fashion #trendy #hygge #blogger #influencer #business #market #b52

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text: i’m doing some writing this morning and came across the notebook that had this rap in it. almost a year ago i went to the dunes and put it on video because it was the only way to get what i was feeling off of my chest. i was too scared to share it publicly, but the words still ring true to me today. it’s not perfect... there is profanity... but it’s important. to believe women. and to believe men. to believe all survivor’s. to not make excuses for your friends. you can’t support a cause but have “exceptions” because you know “he would never.” we have to do better. #believewomen #believesurvivors #metoo #resist #supporteachother #rap #rhyme #aworkinprogress

text:
dziś obchodzimy międzynarodowy dzień kobiet i dziewcząt w nauce🔬stąd najnowszy numer #thelancet,jednego z najbardziej szanowanych medycznych czasopism na świecie, zadedykowany jest właśnie kobietom.kobietom w nauce i medycynie.co ważniejsze,edytorial zatytułowany jest:„feminism is for everybody”i aż ciarki mi po plecach przeszły,gdy to zobaczyłam,bo pomyślałam,jak bardzo wszyscy boją się określenia „feministka”czy„feminista” w polskim środowisku medycznym i w sumie naukowym w ogóle.a tutaj taki tytuł,taki temat przewodni💪 w naukowej prasie💪niespodzianka,nieprawdopodobnie miłe zaskoczenie💞editorial porusza tak ważne kwestie,jak dyskryminacja ze względu na płeć oraz wciąż nierówną reprezentację kobiet i mężczyzn w nauce💔 podsumowuje zawarte w najnowszym numerze artykuły.wskazuje na badania udowadniające,że zespoły niejednolite pod względem płci osiągają lepsze wyniki w pracy i nauce☝zwraca uwagę na krzywdzący w stosunku do kobiet system przyznawania grantów naukowych👎przyznaje, że dyskusja o nierówności płci w medycynie, która jak każda dziedzina nauki jest głęboko utwierdzona w przekonaniu o swoim obiektywizmie i opieraniu się na twardych dowodach,a nie dyskryminacji,jest trudna😔szczęśliwie,the lancet nie boi się o tym mówić publikując w najnowszym numerze artykuły wskazujące na to,jak niektóre działy nauki i medycyny są priorytetyzowane ze względu na płeć,co dla mnie nie jest wielką nowością,ale myślę,że dotychczas nie mówiło się o tym tak otwarcie i nikt nie przywoływał twardych dowodów na takie tezy. thelancet zwraca uwagę,że walka z nierównościami płci w medycynie jest ważna nie tylko ze względu na same kobiety obecne w nauce,nie chodzi tylko o ich prawa i sprawiedliwość,ale też,a może przede wszystkim o dobro i lepszą opiekę dla pacjentów.zauważa,jak ważne,aby dziedziny nauki,które mają służyć człowiekowi,jak medycyna,były reprezentowane zarówno przez kobiety,jak i mężczyzn,a walka o równouprawnienie ze względu na płeć leży w obowiązku wszystkich–kobiet,mężczyzn,osób pracujących w nauce, kierowników i kierowniczek zespołów naukowych.również czasopism medycznych, bo jak mówi tytuł edytorialu feminizm jest dla wszystkich. 
budujące prawda?

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
hoy te traemos un previo de “el mejor hombre que puedes ser”. es el nuevo comercial de gillete que se volvió viral generando polémica por hacer referencia al acoso y al movimiento #metoo logrando resultados abismales de respuestas en contra y a favor de un mensaje hacia la “masculinidad tóxica”. la empresa cree que la fuerte reacción se debe a que el anuncio es un cambio de la forma en la que gillette se promocionaba anteriormente y eso ha sorprendido a la gente.
.
- se vio 4 millones de veces en youtube en 48 horas.
- generó (hasta el momento) 900 mil “dislikes” y 400 mil "likes".
- se consideró una campaña que ataca a su público objetivo.
- su participación en el mercado bajo 20% según datos de forbes.

después de conocer un poco de esta controversia y ver el comercial, cuéntanos ¿cuál es tu hipótesis? ¿cuál fue el error que cometió gillette? leemos tus comentarios.
.
.
#naddspublicidad #comercial #gillete #publicidad #marketing

text:
"no #teenager who is just beginning to navigate the working 
#world should ever have to deal with unwelcome sexual advances 
as part of the hiring process," said charles f. coleman, jr., the 
eeoc lead trial attorney. "the remedial provisions of the consent 
decree are designed to ensure such behavior never occurs again 
at this #restaurant." #eeoc regional attorney jeffrey burstein said, "conditioning 
hiring in exchange for #sexual favors, known as quid-pro-quo 
sexual harassment, is exactly the type of behavior that has made 
the deserved momentum around #metoo continue to grow 
stronger. the eeoc is determined to do its part to ensure sexual 
harassment of this kind is eradicated from the workplace."

text:
april is recognised as sexual assault awareness month,an opportunity to educate people and raise awareness about sexual assault. sexual violence refers to crimes like sexual assault, rape, and sexual abuse. in the united states, 1 in 5 women will be raped in her lifetime,and nearly 1 in 2 women and 1 in 5 men will experience sexual violence victimisation other than rape. 
with the recent #metoo movement, sexual violence has never been such a large part of our national conversation. but what about sexual abuse victims whose abusers are not a stranger or an acquaintance? what about victims who are sexually abused by an intimate partner? our organisation will explore the intersection of domestic violence and sexual assault.
learn about marital rape and discover ways you can take a stand against domestic violence and sexual assault.
do not let anyone control you.
stand up for your ownself.
join us in putting an end to this.
#rapeisrape
#aprilrightsorganisation

text:
aviation: walking in atlanta (8/10) by nicholas jones, 01 january 2017. -

when i was walking in atlanta,
i found myself in flight amidst a night so lit with stars,
i found myself in richest history and piano bars,
looking at people through the windows of their cars,
just so i could carry their faces in my head,
when the time came for me to depart,

when i was walking in atlanta,
one man offered me the rest of his virginia slim,
with a pack stacked to the brim - on a whim,
i decided to take one more from him - just for the hell of it,
and we talked for hours about the ins and outs,
of small town life - catching flights - and counting down the minutes,
as we moved away from midnight - and what a fun night it was,

i would give just about anything in this world,
to recapture that time again - after which the memory ends,
and i find myself pulling petals from flowers,
while writing in my dream journal about what it means to fly,
from here to where i once called home,
because i’ve never felt more comfortable,
than i did when i was walking down the streets,
of atlanta. -

text: no more spoons today. who said therapy is easy? gosh, therapy has absolutely exhausted me recently. i am so lucky and grateful that i have been supported by some great people in the nhs who has referred me to trauma focused therapy. my therapist and me have a great rapport and i’m starting to open up and speak more with less dissociating because of the management there is. it is so hard but so worthy. end the stigma of therapy y’all. therapy is great and shouldn’t be seen as something for ‘people with problems or diagnoses’ therapy is for anyone and everyone. it is a safe, open, confidential place. no shame in therapy. no shame of my mental illnesses. no shame that i am still traumatised. i deserve help and support. you deserve help. 🌻#endtherapystigma

text:
here’s an idea: buy an $891 car that doesn’t work and don’t pay the utility bills so our water gets shut off. this is after weeks of me asking him “what our plan is” to make money specifically to pay the bills...and of course now that i’m upset, i’m the bad guy for showing so. he’s telling me that he couldn’t even have a job because i’d be harassing him the entire time so he wouldn’t even be able to complete his work. isn’t it funny how they have the ability to make everything about them? this is following his phone being shut off a few weeks ago after he was insisting we get a plan together (my parents still pay mine since after he stole my phone over a year ago.) he kept telling me, “we need a plan together to prove to everyone we’re a united front.” no, you wanted a plan with me under my name because yours is delinquent...glad i listened to my gut about something...
.
.
he can be playing nice all he wants, but the narc is still in there! 👌🏼

text: i don’t always feel whole. but i’m not going to stop moving forward. i’m not sure how i made it through alive sometimes. i definitely have scars from it all. i wish i had visible ones sometimes lol. then i could say yeah, see this? this is what happened to me and why i’m a mess sometimes lol. i’m allergic to ink so i can’t get a tattoo. i understand why people get them. if i could i would. bottom line is as long as i’m breathing i’m gonna keep moving forward in this life. ima do the best i can for me and everyone who cares about me. i’m wishing you all a badass week. take care of yourselves out there! do something just for you today. even if it’s only a 20 minute hot bath with a little music. do one thing for you 😉. -vu❤️💜 #vaginasunitedvu

text:
jag har regelbundet börjat att träna antingen på gymm eller så tar jag långa powerwalks. eftersom jag lätt blir uttråkad på gymmet så har jag hittat min grej att intervall träna på löpbandet  att springa / gång. jag utmanar mig själv genom att öka tempot och orka fem minuter till.. 60 min kör jag utan stopp det är mitt mål just nu. 🏃‍♀️
helt ärligt det bästa jag har gjort😀 för min vardagsångest har jag lyckats hålla i schack nu. jag tror också att rädslan att tappa kontrollen har minskat i och med att jag börjat att träna. det är nu exakt tio dagar sen jag vaknade upp med en panikångestattack , jag var verkligen livrädd , hjärtklappning yrsel svårt att andas kräkningar , alla cylindrar var på!! mitt liv var i fara. hjärnspöken men så verkliga just då minns inte ens vad jag drömde om bara att det svarta mörka skulle förgöra mig. just den kvällen mådde jag så extremt bra full med energi och somnade med ett leende på läpparna. 
min psykolog sa till mig att jag inte skulle analysera varför det hände just då utan mer att det inte ör så konstigt med tanke på allt jag har varit med om..
efter den natten var jag helt slut i två dagar , det bara suger allt liv ur dig! 
jag har lärt mig att ta vara på dom bra dagarna. 
jag skulle vilja hinna med mer saker och träffa mina vänner familj oftare ❤️ men mellan jobb och allt annat behöver jag  min återhämtning själv, för att orka med åtaganden och planer jag har lagt. i går tränade jag på att börja läsa i min bok högt , det är en helt annan sak än när man är uppe i skrivandet. 
varje ord, person händelse handlar ju faktiskt om mig, en person jag inte känner. men jag gör det för att det är min historia jag måste bära den med min röst precis som jag tillsammans med mina barn bär vår historia med stolthet på våra axlar så är det nu min tur att nå fram nu när den kommer att bli en ljudbok.🎧📕i lördags umgicks jag  med mina vänner😍#fotografelinnordin#träning#pdst#vännerförlivet #återhämtning#❤️ #ptsd #metoo #kvinnovåld #feminism #kvinnorsrättigheter #kvinnojouren #ptsdawareness #våldinärarelation #christellandersson #humanrights #motivation
#takecontroll #motivationalspeaker

text:
one of the original #metoo heroines. when mukhtaran mai went public, naming the rapists in her village, she broke *multiple rules*. custom dictated that she should kill herself out of shame, but she chose to stay alive. as a woman who is told to hide the violence she survived, she dared to speak out. as a woman from a conservative village, she dared to go public and take up space on national media. 
uff, what unimaginable courage, what commitment to justice.
