text:
do you know that most abusers claim to be religious? a report came out yesterday showing 700 sexual assault victims in 20 years in southern baptist churches. this isn't a baptist problem, and it isn't a catholic problem.  it is an abuser problem.
•
abuse can be found in every faith community.  why? because abusers seek out people that are good, honest, forgiving, trustworthy, and willing to give them the benefit of the doubt. abusers also seek out places they can hide and manipulate. the key to stopping abusers is to be educated and have appropriate policies and accountability systems in place so they can't hide or manipulate.
•
i wrote a blog about the things i learned at the safe environment training for faith communities put on by the gundersen national child protection training center. you can read it at the link in the bio ➡️ faith and child abuse
⛪️
we stop child sexual abuse by taking away the manipulation toolkit from the abuser. we do that by educating, implementing and following proper policies, and having accountability. the main way to stop child abuse is to believe the child.  we have a 100% chance of stopping a predator, if we believe the first child the first time they say the name of their abuser. 💞
#defendsurvivors #believethechild #faith #abuse #religiousabuse #childsexualabuse #childabuse #traumainformed #justiceisprotectionandprevention #csa

text:
some days are just like this. and some aren't. i've gotten pretty good at managing my anxiety over the years, but when life gets overwhelming my anxiety spikes...often because i feel like too much is out of my control. 
that's just it. control. if you are a survivor of trauma, like me, you have had alot of control removed from you. that's scary stuff. however, for me, the more control i surrender to god the less i struggle with my anxiety. i've chosen to not take meds, just not for me. i did for a short period, and it just wasnt right. overall what works for me is my faith, prayer, yoga, music and writing. what works for you?

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

text:
una de nuestras primeras novedades del año en reservoir narrativa, es a la vez un ensayo urgente que busca poner el foco en un problema recurrente y de constante actualidad, y con el que queremos seguir apostando por una línea de pensamiento radical y provocador. ‘violación. aspectos de un crimen, de lucrecia al #metoo’ de mithu m. sanyal, es una de esas obras polémicas y atrevidas, que trata un tema incómodo del que bien poco se ha escrito en la actualidad. con un riguroso discurso y un enfoque rompedor, esta prestigiosa periodista y crítica cultural examina todas las ideas preconcebidas y recoge los aspectos históricos y culturales de este crimen (desde aristóteles al #nomeansno, pasando por ‘la violación de lucrecia’ de shakespeare y las corrientes feministas modernas), para abrir un debate necesario que nos permita encontrar las estrategias más actuales y aplicables para acabar con este crimen de una vez por todas y cambiar la percepción que se tiene de el.
.
#reservoirbooks #narrativa #reservoirnarrativa #ensayo #violación #mithusanyal #mithumsanyal #megustaleer

text:
i have become increasingly confused by the true meaning of feminism the older i get. i thought it was about equality and female empowerment. that we were fighting for a better world with no judgment or gender bias. a world where women could stop seeing each other as competition and instead love each other as kindred spirits. regardless of your life choices.
.
.
i see so much bitterness and bullying every day; fat shaming, skinny shaming, she has loose morals, is bossy, arrogant. no; she is beautiful, confident and enjoys her body, where's the harm? we need to stop being so worried about appearance and about our insecurities so we can truly find peace and equality. until then, i feel as though we are doomed...
.
.
.
.
.

text:
i bland har jag så svårt att förstå hur jag kunde orka leva som jag gjorde i så många många år! när jag tänker på det så är min första tanke jag känner inte den personen vem var hon? 
grubblar mycket på detta i perioder, inte så att jag slår på mig själv men ändå kan inte riktigt släppa. 
genom min psykolog har jag börjat förstå att det sociala arvet min uppväxt har påverkat mig mer än vad jag trodde. det här fotot är väldigt talande. 
tänk att jag under väldigt lång tid spenderade min tid med att titta ner i marken. 
jag var livrädd att någon skulle genomskåda mig och se hur värdelös jag var om jag tilläts mig att våga lyfta huvudet och möta blicken. men aldrig mer! 
i dag vågar jag lyfta huvudet möta din blick och släppa in dig ❤️ jag har så mycket saker jag ska hinna med, varje dag är värdefull jag har redan förlorat så mycket ! men jag har tagit tillbaka mer. 
jag mår rätt så bra just nu 😊 ok sömnen strular fortfarande men jag jobbar på det. jag hoppas jag får se er på min föreläsning i göteborg i mars tillsammans med rsk/ nolltolerans. kramar 🙏💕 #ptsd #metoo #kvinnovåld #feminism #kvinnorsrättigheter #kvinnojouren #ptsdawareness #våldinärarelation #christellandersson #humanrights #motivation
#takecontroll #motivationalspeaker

text:
hbo’s ‘crashing’ smartly takes on pc culture, comedy in the #metoo era
#
close comedian pete holmes of hbo's 'crashing" talks about starting stand up in nyc spoiler alert! contains minor spoilers from the feb. 10 episode of hbo's "crashing." new york – is it a bad time to be a straight white man in comedy?  hardly, but that doesn't stop many of them from saying it. high-profile comedians including jerry seinfeld, louis ck and norm macdonald have all bemoaned that comedy has become too politically correct in recent years – a groan-worthy sentiment that's echoed by (fictional) veteran comic jason (dov davidoff) in sunday's incisive new episode of hbo's "crashing," midway through its third season. "this (expletive) used to be fun; it used to be dangerous," jason tells pete (pete holmes), shortly after bombing with a crude stand-up set about being casually racist and not asking for sexual consent. "if i were a biracial lesbian doing the same material, that crowd would've carried me around – they would've had a parade for me." the episode comes to an ugly climax when jason – furious after female comic ally (jamie lee) calls out his misogyny onstage – drunkenly harasses a waitress, who turns down his aggressive advances. the club docks his pay and he has a heated post-show confrontation with ally, where she likens his…

text:
#recenzja #vox #metoo

kobiety straciły prawa prawie do wszystkiego. mogą powiedzieć tylko 100słów dziennie, bo każde kolejne kończy się porażeniem prądem. naszą narratorką jest jean, która spełnia swoje zadanie matki i pani domu (błąd- niewolnicy domu). nikt nie jest gorzej traktowany, niż kobiety. to mężczyźni są górą a one "spełniają swoją funkcję". ten bardzo dziwny i niesprawiedliwy świat prezentuje nam #wydawnictwomuza w swojej najnowszej książce. 
pierwszy rozdział chwycił mnie za serce i serio zrobiło mi się smutno. narratorką jest kobieta, która ma doktorat z lingwistyki, a teraz nie może czytać książek, pouczać synów a nawet zaśpiewać na dobranoc kołysanki swojej córce. bardzo mnie to zabolało. 
później jeszcze bardziej książka mnie interesowała, ale gdzieś w połowie zaczęło się wszystko gubić. liczne tajemnice rządowe, sekrety, niewiadome... za dużo tego i doprowadziło to do lekkiego zamieszania. pogubiłem się i trudno było mi później czytać.

książka jest naprawdę ciekawa do pewnego momentu, później jest zagmatwana a zakończenie trochę naciągane. w końcu bohaterką nie jest nastolatka, która się przeciwstawia systemowi, tylko dorosła kobieta z charakterem. mimo wszystko cieszę się, że mogłem przeczytać tę książkę, bo niesie ze osobą hasło równouprawnienia. mam nadzieję, że nigdy nie dojdzie do tego, o czym napisała #christinadalcher

text:
when you fall in love for the first time, or second, or gazillionth, everything feels possible. your opportunities expand, your world broadens. you get to try new foods because you’re dating someone from a different culture. you get to celebrate in different ways because every family does things a bit differently. you meet new people because your circle of friends gets bigger. in a word, everything feels roomy.
when you’re in an unhealthy relationship, things don’t feel quite as possible. your world tends to narrow, your opportunities to hang out with people or do things you used to enjoy decrease. the person you’re dating doesn’t like your friends, so you stop hanging out with them. you stop spending time on your hobbies because the person you’re dating wants to spend all their time with you. you start wondering what you should wear because the person you’re dating always comments on your outfits. things feel squished. does your valentine make you feel like your floating and free?  you deserve to have and offer kind of love!  see www.wscadv.org to learn how. #llt #lovelikethis #huddleup #februaryisteendatingviolenceawarenessmonth #tdvam2019 #tdvam

text:
karena kebanyakan kesaksian korban kekerasan seksual justru tidak dipercaya 🙄
•
makanya kami butuh jaminan rasa aman dari kekerasan seksual dan juga jaminan dari berbagai resiko-resiko yang mengikutinya agar produktifitas kami sebagai perempuan muda tidak terhambat gara-gara kekerasan seksual.
•
jika ruu p-ks tidak segera disahkan, sama halnya dengan membiarkan kami terus dihantui rasa tidak aman dan bayang-bayang resiko menjadi korban kekerasan seksual.
•
jika ruu p-ks tidak segera disahkan, sama halnya dengan membiarkan korban semakin bertambah dan tidak mendapatkan keadilan.

text: haven’t been posting much, i’ve just been concentrating on getting well, but i want to talk about something really important today. please don’t roll your eyes because it’s a topic you hear about everywhere, it needs to be discussed by everyone who has gone through it so we can see just how prolific it is, and that’s sexual exploitation. i have always said my abuse took place at home and it was non-sexual, just physically violent and emotionally damaging. this is true about my abuse at home, but the fact is my abuse didn’t end at home. i left home many times either because i was kicked out for daring to defend myself as i got older, or i would get sick of getting beat up and i would leave. but a young teenage girl is not equipped to live out in the world on her own. yesterday is the first time i ever heard the term “survival sex“. i was an extremely sexually active teenager, i also engaged in many high-risk behaviors and used drugs very regularly, particularly opiates. there were times i found myself sleeping on the couch of some random guy and they would suggest sex or coerce me into sex in exchange for a place to stay and i would give in most of the time because, when it comes down to brass tacks, i was afraid for my safety if i said no but i fooled myself into believing it was consensual. not to mention, nobody wants to sleep outside in the midst of michigan winter. i would exchange places to stay for sex pretty regularly, i recalled at least 10 or 12 situations like that last night and i’m sure there were many more. one of them was incredibly threatening, he approached me in the middle of the night while i was sleeping on his basement floor. i pretended to sleep at the beginning, and then just went along with it because he was super high and huge compared to me and i was afraid. it has taken me 40 years to recognize that i was sexually exploited and in that particular situation, raped. because my physical abuse at home groomed me to believe i was the one screwing up. i was the one putting myself in bad situations. i never knew what to call that "gray area", consenting to sex that did not feel consensual. it’s not gray. it’s black and white. cont' in comments

text: holy smoke! what do you say to these? those of you who have been following me for a while know that i sometimes also present the work of other artists in my feed. they might have caught my attention due to their message, unusual techniques or simply colours that talk to me. these incredibly expressive dog sculptures were created by helen thompson (who works under the name ‘holy smoke’ 😜), an artist living in the uk. each piece is unique and handcrafted using unusual materials such as wire, natural linen and vintage textiles. the imperfections of the materials and their raw edges bring the sculptures to life and give them character. in order to give the finished pieces patina, thomson often slightly burns the edges, hence her pseudonym ‘holy smoke’. i am reminded of streetwise stray dogs. don’t you think her dogs are just heartbreakingly real and fragile?

text:
i wrote this song long time ago when i arrived to mallorca (spain) ... i used to play a 'blues song' very similar and i had the idea to make something like that but with my own message and sound.
this song talks about "the bad communication between the people"... about all the things you don't say and the sad moments that those things create inside of you... and even when you love someone that much but you missunderstand each other, the reality is that this relation has the big risk to break. :/
i composed "silence of love" for my sister silvana with all my loving and i think she loves it 😍 and now, i dedicate specially to all this crazy world.

if you wanna listen the complete song, follow me on #spotify & #deeser and with lyrics, on #youtube. 😘😘 -----
compuse esta canción hace mucho tiempo cuando llegué a mallorca por primera vez. 
solía tocar un blues muy similar con esta energia, hasta que derrepente me surgieron las ganas de hacer algo parecido pero con mi propio sonido, dando mi propio mensaje. 
así es que 'silence' habla de la "mala comunicación entre las personas", acerca de todas esas cosas que no nos decimos, nos guardamos, no resolvemos y que terminan causando infinitos momentos de tristeza.

sabiendo que esa situación puede quebrar cualquier tipo de relación, aunque exista muchísimo amor de por medio. :(
compuse esta canción para mi hermana silvana con mucho cariño y creo que a ella le encanta 😋, y hoy, se la dedico a este loco mundo entero. :)
espero que les guste!
y para escuchar la versión completa, siganme en @spotify y @deezer!
y con la letra, lo encontrarán en #you tube.

text: a little over a year ago, i made a handful of videos. 🎥 in them, i shared my 20 year secret of sexual abuse as a child and some insights while navigating the healing process. ❤️ i quickly questioned what i really had to offer and stopped. a few months ago someone left a comment on one of my videos. (that have unfortunately been taken down.) in part, it said, 🔥🔥...”when you said, you have no credentials, well i can tell you, there is no book that can teach you what you already lived through. ppl like yourself, are the best, because you can relate.”🔥🔥🔥 i don’t know if i’ll make more videos, although it was encouraging to know they were helpful. this is to anyone that is feeling #impostersyndrome - keep going! ❤️you do have the skills. 🧡you are needed. 💛 #motivationmonday

(that have unfortunately been taken down.) in part, it said, 🔥🔥...”when you said, you have no credentials, well i can tell you, there is no book that can teach you what you already lived through. ppl like yourself, are the best, because you can relate.”🔥🔥🔥 i don’t know if i’ll make more videos, although it was encouraging to know they were helpful. this is to anyone that is feeling #impostersyndrome - keep going! ❤️you do have the skills. 🧡you are needed. 💛 #motivationmonday

text: this morning i was listening to one of my favorite podcasts, @deathsexmoney, on the subject of #metoo...the host stated that she would count to three and asked that everyone who had been touched or violated say, me too in unison. this movement is not new, but i was surprised that i could utter the phrase in one breath and think to myself, “but what woman hasn’t been touched or talked dirty to in some way they don’t like,” in the next breath. this is just part of being a woman, right?? well, it fucking shouldn’t be...why am i posting a picture of hawthorne berries with this? it’s because this herb is pretty amazing in its actions on the ❤️ heart. whether it’s physical or emotional trauma, hawthorne has a way of gently shifting this energy in a positive direction. today’s epiphany over🙂.

text:
i was born and brought up in the us and was lucky to have had so many privileges growing up. however, not everyone is as lucky and that is something i realized early on in life. hence, i started “gyaan ghar” learning centre at the age of 15, which is a tutoring centre located in ludhiana, punjab that provides extracurricular instructions to low-income students in new lajpat nagar. while growing up in the us, i used to arrange a fundraiser in school every year, where if each student donated 5 usd, which is somewhere around 350 indian rupees, it could help run the learning centre for an entire year! this made me realize that it doesn’t take much, to just reach out and put in a little effort to help someone in some way.
we started off with 10 students and today, we have 65 students enrolled, with two full time teachers and amazing volunteers who also act like extra-curricular instructors on a daily basis. of course none of this would have been possible without my grandma who is the de facto principal of “gyaan ghar” and oversees the daily functioning of the centre. even at the age of 80, she does it with so much gusto and enthusiasm! it is her commitment to creating a change in the community that drives me to do the same as well.
after completing my graduation in economics from harvard, i permanently moved to india to work with aangan india, which is a non-profit organization dedicated to reducing child harm in the forms of trafficking, early marriage, labour, and violence. i have a deeply personal passion for working on making women and children safer. especially with the #metoo movement all around us, it feels really important to lend a voice to those who may not even have the visibility to say 'me too.’ i believe that those of us who are lucky enough to be born with privilege have a responsibility to lift others up with us.
#kindnessunlimited
- ratna gill @aangan_trust
name: Kindness Unlimited

text:
à l’époque (2009-2012), le harcèlement était encore moins combattu en france qu’aujourd’hui. c’est ce qui a, entre autre, permis à ce groupe facebook, la ligue du lol, de prospérer en ciblant bon nombre d’internautes à coups d’insultes, montages et autres menaces. principalement sur internet, parfois en dehors (appels téléphoniques, visite sur le lieu de travail). la plupart des prises pour cible étaient des femmes qui se lançaient dans le blogging et le journalisme. avec des propos soutenant la cause féminine, les lgbt+ et les minorités. surnommé le « 18-25 avant l’heure », ce qui surprend avec la ligue du lol est la composition du groupe —> principalement des trentenaires qui versent… dans le blogging et le journalisme.
pompeux, arrogants et « malaisants », cette bande de potes utilise l’art de la plume pour le pire. en menant des campagnes de cyber-harcèlement sur des internautes qui, aujourd’hui, prennent la parole. si le fait de dénoncer ce type d’attitude était so difficile à l’époque, c’est aussi parce que les harceleurs étaient des « confrères ». parfois des collègues. aujourd’hui, libération a annoncé la mise à pied de l’un des journalistes concernés, alexandre hervaud. de même, brain magazine et nouvelles écoutes ont annoncé mettre fin à leur collaboration avec les journalistes vincent glad et guilhem malissen. stephen des aulnois, rédacteur en chef du tag parfait, a remis sa démission. 
si ces sanctions sont une bonne chose, de nombreuses personnes harcelées à l’époque des faits soulignent, au fil de leurs témoignages, qu’il y avait une trentaine de sales types du genre. christophe carron, rédacteur en chef de slate. david doucet, rédacteur en chef web des inrocks. entre autre. le harcèlement doit être nommé. le harcèlement doit être puni.

text_retweet: posted @withrepost • @earthlove777 rp @erinrileycarrasco i didn’t become vegan because i didn’t like the way meat and dairy tasted. i became vegan because i hated the taste of cruelty and suffering. so many people don’t know this, so here’s the truth: all calves born in the dairy industry are “bi-products.” all dairy cows need to be pregnant to produce milk. they don’t just produce milk on their own. farmers then steal the milk meant for the calves and sell to humans to drink. most calves are taken from their mother within the first 24 hours and either slaughtered or if a boy, sent to veal sheds where they are isolated in a tiny shed for apprx 5 months and then slaughtered. female calves may be spared, but are destined to live the same life as their mother and between 4-5 yrs of age, are also slaughtered after a life of being confined, put on the rape rack and having their babies stolen over and over. their bodies are spent after years of milk ”production” and then their flesh is sold to meat eaters. in the wild, cows live upwards of 20 years. you’re not going to hear about this on mainstream media. why do you think that is? that’s the truth. that’s dairy and that is cruelty. just because you like the taste of cheese does not negate the fact that this is what you’re paying for. #februdairy #dairyfree #dairy #govegan #crueltyfree #meat #hamburger #burger #pizzahut #pizzapizza #ilovepizza #cheesecake #cheesecakefactory #cheesey #vegetarian #creamy #cream #creamcheese #dairyisscary #stopseparatingfamilies #burgerking #veggies #farmher #vegano #metoo #seperation #donttakeourplanetforgranted

🍃🌱alni body care unflavored cbd tincture (cbd oil). available in 3 strengths. made with lab-tested colorado hemp cbd isolate, 0% thc.  ingest sublingually, or add to your morning coffee, smoothie, salad dressing, or any favorite recipe without altering taste.  many of you know that i use cbd products for pain, but i actually first started using cbd to treat my anxiety from ptsd and wean off pharmaceutical anxiety medications.  working my vending tables is extremely stressful for me; i wouldn’t be able to do it without taking my cbd tincture. even long before the trauma that caused my ptsd, i suffered from crippling social anxiety. from the ages 17-21 i used alcohol to feel more comfortable in social situations, which can be extremely dangerous for many reasons.  i drank in excess and drank  to black  out; it was more than just the “college drinking” type, i wanted to be absent from the moment entirely to escape from the “icky” feeling of socializing and talking to people.  after my trauma, i eventually stopped drinking, since it reminded me of what happened, but was then prescribed klonopin and subsequently valium + effexor for my ptsd and anxiety.  these medications, in my opinion, should only be used temporarily as a band aid, not long term. i was on them for a few years. they made my anxiety extremely worse, and i became dependent on them, since they allowed me to “black out” without drinking and avoid connecting and socializing with people.  i even had to take tylenol pm at night to help me sleep, since my body became used to the meds. it changed my personality and i had several seizures from missed doses.  finally, when i moved to colorado, i discovered cbd for anxiety/ptsd and found a great doctor who helped me properly wean down off my medications safely.  i am now over 2+ years free from rx anxiety meds and i have never felt better.  i use cbd only for pain, anxiety, and sleep + thc for nausea. if anyone is curious about cbd for anxiety or ptsd, please feel free to reach out.💜💜💜 happy to help anyone live a better life naturally. 🍃🌱

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
- she [rebekah mercer] loved me. she was like, oh we need more of your type on our side!

your type? - the gays. she loved the gays. so did steve [bannon]. he saw us as early adopters. he figured, if you can get the gays on board, everyone else will follow. it’s why he was so into the whole milo [yiannopoulos] thing.

robert mercer was a pioneer in ai and machine translation. he helped invent algorithmic trading – which replaced hedge fund managers with computer programs – and he listened to wylie’s pitch. it was for a new kind of political message-targeting based on an influential and groundbreaking 2014 paper researched at cambridge’s psychometrics centre, called: - computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans. - in politics, the money man is usually the dumbest person in the room. whereas it’s the opposite way around with mercer, says wylie. - he said very little, but he really listened. he wanted to understand the science. and he wanted proof that it worked.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

robe mercer was a pioneer in ai and machine translation. he helped invent algorithmic trading – which replaced hedge fund managers with computer programs – and he listened to wylie’s pitch. it was for a new kind of political message-targeting based on an influential and groundbreaking 2014 paper researched at cambridge’s psychometrics centre, called: - computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans. - in politics, the money man is usually the dumbest person in the room. whereas it’s the opposite way around with mercer, says wylie. - he said very little, but he really listened. he wanted to understand the science. and he wanted proof that it worked.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
she fled saudi arabia in january of this year to escape her abusive family who she believed would kill her for renouncing islam. she originally fled to thailand where immigration officials attempted to deport her back to the middle east. through her cunning use of social media to document her arrival and subsequent detention, a global campaign set fire to support her asylum. on january 12th, rahaf was granted asylum status in canada  after a delayed response from australia, her preferred country of resettlement. rahaf is now safely in canada where she stands as a powerful figure of defiance against saudi arabia’s male guardianship system preventing women from autonomous decision making across all critical aspects of their lives including freedom to travel
.
a arábia saudita ela fugiu em janeiro deste ano para escapar de sua família abusiva, que ela acreditava que iria matá-la por renunciar ao islã. ela originalmente fugiu para a tailândia, onde as autoridades de imigração tentaram deportá-la de volta ao oriente médio. através de seu uso astuto de mídia social para documentar sua chegada e subsequente detenção, uma campanha global incendiou seu asilo. em 12 de janeiro, rahaf recebeu o status de asilo no canadá depois de uma resposta tardia da austrália, seu país preferido de reassentamento. rahaf está agora em segurança no canadá, onde se apresenta como uma poderosa figura de desafio contra o sistema de tutela masculina da arábia saudita, impedindo as mulheres de tomar decisões autónomas em todos os aspectos críticos das suas vidas, incluindo a liberdade de viajar
.
#feminism #feminismo #metoo #timesup #smashthepatriarchy #neverthelessshepersisted #elenao #genderequality
.

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
a trailblazing brazilian feminist activist on a mission to end global human trafficking operations led by religious cult leaders such as joão de deus and prem baba, as well as broader sexual abuse taking place inside spiritual organizations. sabrina,  recently discovered dead in what is believed to be a framed political suicide, was instrumental in exposing human trafficking operations that would coerce poor (usually black) women in rural parts of brazil into bonded sexual slavery. she exposed to the world the “women farms” where women given food in return for offering their bodies to carry newborns that would then be brought to adoption markets in western nations. as has been the case throughout herstory when it comes to women exposing the underbelly of patriarchy, bittencourt’s groundbreaking activism has been notoriously disregarded to the point where her death is being quickly swept under the rug. bittencourt’s work, continues to be carried out through the coame movement (combatting abuse inside the spiritual)
.
uma ativista feminista brasileira pioneira em uma missão para acabar com operações globais de tráfico de seres humanos lideradas por líderes de cultos religiosos como joão de deus e prem baba, bem como abusos sexuais mais amplos ocorrendo dentro de organizações espirituais. sabrina, recentemente descoberta morta no que se acredita ser um suicídio político emoldurado, foi fundamental para expor as operações de tráfico de seres humanos que coagiriam mulheres pobres (normalmente negras) nas zonas rurais do brasil a escravidão sexual. ela expôs ao mundo as "fazendas de mulheres", onde as mulheres recebiam comida em troca de oferecer seus corpos para transportar recém-nascidos que seriam levados a adotar mercados em países ocidentais. o ativismo revolucionário de bittencourt tem sido notoriamente ignorado até o ponto em que sua morte é rapidamente varrida para debaixo do tapete. o trabalho de bittencourt continua sendo realizado através do movimento coame (combate ao abuso no meio espiritual)
.
#feminism #feminismo #metoo #timesup #smashthepatriarchy #neverthelessshepersisted #elenao #genderequality

text:
when a project is constructed around nudity and equated with freedom, does a woman who chooses not to disrobe for any reason then live in permanent unfreedom? how does one photograph women naked and interpret that as “power” when women in india, especially dalit and adivasi, are regularly stripped as punishment?

#metoo isn't just about harassment/direct sexual violence and shouldn't be reduced to that. there are other forms of violence and harassment that occupy the dominant ways in which scholarship, art, technology is produced. our second essay on #metoo takes apart the ethics of photography as they exist in india and internationally. when we contacted people for this piece, they literally began pulling images off their websites. details when you read.

this piece has spent a long time in post-production where our editorial team has debated the use of images, consent and despaired deeply about the state of photography as an art in india. we are blessed to have such wonderful people who spoke to us - some anonymously and others openly - to help us bring a discussion of ethics in photography to a wider audience. a huge thank you to everyone who has collaborated with us on the writing of this piece written by @suchitravijayan 
@herdsceneand 
https://www.thepolisproject.com/misogyny-and-racism-as-spectacle-and-performance-a-critique-of-mahesh-shantarams-the-african-portraits-and-forbidden-love/#.xggzebponds

uma ativista feminista brasileira pioneira em uma missão para acabar com operações globais de tráfico de seres humanos lideradas por líderes de cultos religiosos como joão de deus e prem baba, bem como abusos sexuais mais amplos ocorrendo dentro de organizações espirituais. sabrina, recentemente descoberta morta no que se acredita ser um suicídio político emoldurado, foi fundamental para expor as operações de tráfico de seres humanos que coagiriam mulheres pobres (normalmente negras) nas zonas rurais do brasil a escravidão sexual. ela expôs ao mundo as "fazendas de mulheres", onde as mulheres recebiam comida em troca de oferecer seus corpos para transportar recém-nascidos que seriam levados a adotar mercados em países ocidentais. o ativismo revolucionário de bittencourt tem sido notoriamente ignorado até o ponto em que sua morte é rapidamente varrida para debaixo do tapete. o trabalho de bittencourt continua sendo realizado através do movimento coame (combate ao abuso no meio espiritual)
.
#feminism #feminismo #metoo #timesup #smashthepatriarchy #neverthelessshepersisted #elenao #genderequality
.

text:
cardi b
a united states rapper, singer, songwriter from the bronx, new york city who just became the first female solo artist in the history of the grammy awards to win the award for best rap album. her accomplishment marks an important moment within her music genre (a notoriously male dominated and overtly misogynistic arena) as well as more broadly across popular music widely criticized for its misogyny to this day.  cardi’s win stands testament not only her own work as an artist, but to the work of female artists worldwide and throughout herstory, whose creations challenge stereotypes and occupy space despite the direct, cultural, and structural violence working to silence them
. 
um rapper, cantora, e compositora dos estados unidos (de the bronx, nova york), que acabou de se tornar o primeiro artista solo feminino na história do grammy awards para ganhar o prêmio de melhor álbum de rap. sua realização marca um momento importante dentro de seu gênero musical (uma arena notoriamente dominada pelos homens e abertamente misógina), bem como de forma mais ampla na música popular, amplamente criticada por sua misoginia até hoje. a vitória de cardi evidencia não apenas seu próprio trabalho como artista, mas também o trabalho de artistas femininas em todo o mundo e em toda a herística, cujas criações desafiam os estereótipos e ocupam espaço apesar da violência direta, cultural e estrutural que trabalha para silenciá-las
.

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
journalistes parisiens bobo (bourgeois bohème pour les étrangers ) de merde harcelaient des femmes artistes et journalistes... 🤮

créateur du groupe : vincent glad. 🤢

vous échappez pas, on veut les 40 noms des harceleurs 👎... en place publique 📷📷📷 on veut voir vos sales gueules. et #alexandrehervaud de s’excuser d’avoir harcelé durant 11 ans : pathétique... et ensuite #daviddoucet montrez vos gueules ! #stephendesaulnois suivant !

des témoignages dénoncent d’anciens agissements de figures du journalisme web. plusieurs d’entre elles ont déjà reconnu les faits.

c’est l’histoire d’un groupe d’amis virtuel passé de l’humour noir à l’humiliation en meute. jusqu’à atteindre, parfois, l’intimidation physique. le monde des médias est secoué par une affaire de cyberharcèlement depuis la publication, ce week-end sur le site de libération, de témoignages incriminant plusieurs figures du journalisme web.
ces dizaines d’histoires mettent notamment en lumière le rôle obscur joué par la « ligue du lol », un groupe facebook privé créé en 2009 par le journaliste vincent glad. il a regroupé une trentaine de journalistes, communicants et publicitaires parisiens, particulièrement en vue dans le microcosme que constituait twitter au début des années 2010.

text_retweet:
#repost @earthlove777
・・・
rp @erinrileycarrasco i didn’t become vegan because i didn’t like the way meat and dairy tasted. i became vegan because i hated the taste of cruelty and suffering. so many people don’t know this, so here’s the truth: all calves born in the dairy industry are “bi-products.” all dairy cows need to be pregnant to produce milk. they don’t just produce milk on their own. farmers then steal the milk meant for the calves and sell to humans to drink. most calves are taken from their mother within the first 24 hours and either slaughtered or if a boy, sent to veal sheds where they are isolated in a tiny shed for apprx 5 months and then slaughtered. female calves may be spared, but are destined to live the same life as their mother and between 4-5 yrs of age, are also slaughtered after a life of being confined, put on the rape rack and having their babies stolen over and over. their bodies are spent after years of milk ”production” and then their flesh is sold to meat eaters. in the wild, cows live upwards of 20 years. you’re not going to hear about this on mainstream media. why do you think that is? that’s the truth. that’s dairy and that is cruelty. just because you like the taste of cheese does not negate the fact that this is what you’re paying for. #februdairy #dairyfree #dairy #govegan #crueltyfree #meat #hamburger #burger #pizzahut #pizzapizza #ilovepizza #cheesecake #cheesecakefactory #cheesey #vegetarian #creamy #cream #creamcheese #dairyisscary #stopseparatingfamilies #burgerking #veggies #farmher #vegano #metoo #seperation #donttakeourplanetforgranted

text:
“these two are why i do everything”
as a mom, i 100% get this statement, and it rings true in my life in a lot of ways. but don’t just do something for them. do something for you! it’s okay to want to have something that’s just for you!
.
it’s okay to want your own money.
it’s okay to want your own time.
.
as moms we give and give and often go without to ensure everyone else is fine.
.
it’s okay to not be fine!
it’s okay to need help.
it’s for goodness sake it’s okay not to have your sh*t together.
give yourself grace.
.
do something for you. even something small. you can’t give from an empty cup.

text: part 1... sex offender registries identify convicted sex offenders that may be residing in your community. you can search using various criteria including the sex offender's name, gender, race, and address. you can also perform a broader search to identify the number of sex offenders within a given county, city or zip code. the registry also provides a photo of the offender so you will know them if you see them. two additional pieces of information provided are their registry classification (i.e. - sex offender, sexually dangerous predator, absconder) and the type of crime they committed. have you viewed the registry for your community? if so, what did you learn and how did you feel about it? #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist #super bowl

text:
kicking off the new week with some serious local news👓 
offenses such as rape, domestic violence and stalking will be severely punished as of wednesday. up until now, the minimum serving time for such crimes was 6 months and convicted criminals often got away with parole. even chancellor sebastian kurz commented on the matter saying “when minor white-collar crime is punished more harshly in austria than violence against women and children, which often results in lifelong psychological and physical damage, then something is very wrong. we now seek to correct that.” sentences will now be raised to 1-10 years. change is coming! what do you think? #dontbeastranger

text:
инструкция по уходу за бабочкой:
⠀
✨как кормить бабочку
⠀
бабочку необходимо кормить 1-2 раза в день сладкой водичкой (вода с мёдом), апельсинами или переспелыми бананами. 
к сожалению, бабочка не сможет сама найти оставленную еду, поэтому вам будет необходимо самостоятельно пересаживать её "к столу".
⠀
✨где держать бабочку
⠀
если у вас в квартире тепло (+20 с и выше) бабочки будут себя нормально чувствовать.
три раза в день их необходимо опрыскивать из цветочного распылителя.
на ночь лучше посадить в коробку. по одной бабочке в одну коробку! в коробку также нужно положить ватку смоченную в воде, чтобы в коробке было влажно.
⠀
✨локализация:
⠀
сделав несколько кругов, бабочки обычно успокаиваются и рассаживаются на стены, мебель, люстры и т.д.
поскольку бабочки могут сидеть где угодно, в том числе и на полу, чтобы случайно не наступить на бабочек, предупредите ваших гостей о необходимости двигаться аккуратно, смотреть под ноги.
⠀
✨ответственность:
⠀
живая бабочка – существо крайне нежное и уязвимое.
помните, что, приобретая бабочек, вы берёте на себя ответственность за их жизнь.
⠀
👆кормите бабочек и бережно ухаживайте за ними и тогда они будут радовать вас как можно дольше!
name: Живые бабочки🦋Цветы🌺Москва

.

today is the fourth anniversary of the tragic murders of deah, yusor and razan, aka #ourthreewinners. they were killed in their own home in chapel hill,  north carolina. four years later, our hearts are still heavy with grief. those of us in the arab and muslim american communities know it could have been any of us on the other side of craig hicks’ gun...
through my friendship with deah’s older sister, suzanne barakat, i’ve seen how there is no recovering from such tragedy and loss and how the pain never leaves you. but what can do to honor deah, yusor and razan's memory is commit to preventing further hate violence and raising awareness implicit biases. 
learn more and support here: 
launchgood.com/ourthreewinners. #politics #feminist #feminism #london #blogger #smashpatriarchy #justice #metoo #timesup

text:
sounds great but how?
those layers of shit that dimmed your fucking shine have a tendency to build up. 
layer on layer and we wonder, 
if it’s even possible to get out from under the weights
it totally is possible 
i tried to get out from under the layers.  i really did
i tried to remove all the weight and it kept not working
you know what worked?
connection.  the only difference between the women who can sidestep the layers and shine and the ones who keep adding layers of evidence that it won’t work- again?
second chakra work. 
just try this today- rather than listen for a place to respond in conversations just listen to connect.  rather than think we know where someone is headed with a conversation, listen to connect. 
your hearts are already connected.  just like metronomes we beat in sync with who we are around

you totally got this

text:
it was indeed an awesome and eye-opening session at the 3rd edition of who's that girl 2019 @wtg_nigeria . our managing partner mr adesanmi adebunmi @imentorsanmi joined mrs oyinda ige ceo of @the_nest_creche , mrs adenike babalola ceo of  @denikechips and mr jibril abdulrahim a consultant psychiatrist, uch in giving the young boys a charge to treat all the ladies as queens that they truly are. also in attendance was mrs funsho adegbola director, the vale college @thevalecollege

enough is enough with rape, sexual assaults and abuse. we need to raise a generation of men who from being young boys are made to understand that there's no strength in 'overpowering' a lady; there's no strength in being a bully and it's time we made them know that no simply means no. 
kudos to mrs ronke giwa-onafuwa @ronkegiwa1 for this laudable project and congratulations for a hugely successful 3rd edition 'who's that girl', 2019. next edition will be even better and greater. 
#wtg #risconsult #nomeansno #notosexualabuse #girl #metoo
#queens

kudos to mrs ronke giwa-onafuwa @ronkegiwa1 for this laudable project and congratulations for a hugely successful 3rd edition 'who's that girl', 2019. next edition will be even better and greater.

text:
według raportu o przemocy seksualnej “przełamać tabu”, przeprowadzonego przez fundację na rzecz równości i emancypacji ster (http://www.fundacjaster.org.pl/upload/raport-steru-do-netu.pdf polecam się zapoznać), aż 87,6% badanych kobiet doświadczyło jednej lub kilku form molestowania seksualnego, odkąd skończyły 15. rok życia. 77,5% z nich musiało wysłuchiwać nieprzyzwoitych dowcipów i uczestniczyć w natarczywych rozmowach o podtekście seksualnym. 49,6% było dotykane w sposób seksualny lub nakłaniane do pocałunku wbrew swojej woli. 23,1% doświadczyło próby gwałtu, a 22,4% została zgwałcona. najczęściej w swoim własnym domu. •
jedną z konsekwencji #metoo było tsunami głosów, że feministki wydały wyrok na kulturę uwodzenia. “jak mamy w takim razie flirtować?!”. patrząc na te statystyki, zadałabym raczej pytanie: “czy warto bronić takiego etosu romantycznego, który prowadzi do realnej krzywdy?”. czemu pytanie o zgodę ma być automatycznie postrzegane jako zabójcze dla seksualnego podniecenia?
•
masz ochotę? zapytaj mnie czule.

masz wątpliwości? zapytaj mnie czule.
•
to my decydujemy o tym, co jest sexy lub nie. konsensualny seks jest sexy. i niech w końcu to będzie jasne. #askmetender

nähdään ensi viikolla!

-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
michele pred's (@michelepred), "power of the purse" at saks for free! (@freepublicart), brickell city centre, december 6-9, 2018.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the title of power of the purse is inspired by the recent passage of republican tax reform and its far-reaching negative implications for women’s rights. it is also a call to action for women, and men, to redouble their efforts to fight the growth of moneyed privileged and show up at the polls.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the purses are meant to be carried and serve as small-scale political billboards. the text on each purse is created using electroluminescent wire that is lit up using batteries and a small electronic driver.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
“when i sing, the bad memories disappear.” - sandra

today’s #musicmonday is one that is deeply personal to me - and a source of great humility and pride. working for the past 10 years with #makemusicmatter has been a roller coaster to say the least. but today i can honestly say that we have something special going on. today’s song is an example of the power that music has to heal the soul. 
sandra was a participant in our flagship #healinginharmony program at the panzi hospital in the democratic republic of congo. through the program she was able to tell her story - in her own words - through song. the experience transformed her - and all participants into artists. not victims. artists. it is people like her that make the past 10 years of challenges worth it. so today i honour her journey and that of all the people involved in making this crazy dream come true. 
#practicallyawesome #musicheals #bebest #metoo #denismukwege #nobel #peaceprize #yougotthis #artists4artists #positivepsychology #love #survivor #warsucks #bethechange #mentalhealth #ptsd #depression #anxiety #musictherapy

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

[kobiety za stery. magdalena rybicka. strategiczne awanse w zdrojowej] 🙋‍♀️magda rybicka, dotychczasowo dyrektor ds. sprzedaży, została członkiem zarządu zdrojowa hotels. odpowiada za sprzedaż, w tym współdecyduje o strategii rozwoju całej sieci, wraz z otwarciami nowych hoteli, a także sprawne funkcjonowanie hotelowych recepcji. 🏅
www.markajestkobieta.pl 🏅
ma ponad czternastoletnie doświadczenie w hotelarstwie. pracę w tej branży rozpoczynała w intercontinental hotel group, następnie kontynuowała karierę w sieciach hilton i starwood. będąc managerem ds. zakwaterowania podczas uefa euro 2012™ miała doskonałą okazję, aby poznać obiekty noclegowe również od strony klienta. absolwentka szkoły głównej handlowej, posługuje się 3 językami obcymi. prywatnie spędza wolny czas z rodziną i oddaje się swoim pasjom, którymi są: podróże, latanie na paralotni oraz narciarstwo.

pernah ngalamin dulu,, sering,, dari pas masih mi yg belum mudeng kalo perbuatan seperti itu adalah pelecehan, sampe sma yg udah mudeng, masih jg dpt pelecehan,, sedih euy,, mau ngadu ke siapa, pernah ngadu juga dicuekin,, jijay sama manusia2 ituu,, naudzubillah,, be aware para perempuaann,, jangan takut untuk melawan, and say no!! untuk para pelaku, ato yang merasa pernah berbuat seperti itu, plis stop it! itu sangat menjijikkan!! karena perbuatan seperti itu meninggalkan bekas yang tidak akan pernah bisa dilupakan, dan itu sangat menyakitkan!! semoga anak2 ku dijauhkan dari orang2 seperti ituu,, aamiinn
sudah memaafkan, tapi gabisa dilupakan,, tiap kali inget,, sakit ati bgt! 
ini pun sambil ngetik masih dongkol banget, ingin rasanya ku sleding mereka! 😡😡😤😤😤

just found these two old newspapers from 40 years ago. we see this stuff a lot as we update and renovate. the thing that got me was not so much the price 7p, but the language of the sun when talking about laurie cunningham. who? yeah that what i was thinking too but it just goes to show how much we've moved on since then. 
the daily star had a story about margaret thatcher, even though she had only been prime minister for a few weeks she was already closing shipyards.

text: evettt, grammy ile ilgili posttumu da paylaşıp bir sonraki seneye kadar susuyorum. 😃 bildiğiniz üzere alicia keys, gecenin sunucusuydu ve açılışını yaparken sahneye lady gaga, jada pinkett smith, michelle obama ve jenifer lopez’i çağırdı ve açılışa onlar da ortak oldu diyebilirim. #metoo hareketini önceki postlardan birinde anlatmıştım, aslında yaptıkları tüm konuşmalar bununla ilgiliydi. gaga, en başta onu tuhaf bulduklarını ama bunu müziğiyle nasıl yendiğini anlattı, diğerleri de aynı şekilde. daha sonra michelle obama; “i̇ster country sevin, ister rap ya da rock. fark etmiyor. müzik acılarımızı, umutlarımızı, mutluluklarımızı ve onurumuzu paylaşmamızı sağlıyor. birbirimizi duymamıza, davet etmemize vesile oluyor. bize her şeyin bir öneminin olduğunu gösteriyor. her hikayedeki seslerin, her notadaki şarkıların... doğru mu hanımlar?" diyerek noktaladı konuşmayı. en son alicia keys, beyonce’nin şarkısındaki sözleri kullanarak buranın hakimi aslında biz kadınlarız dedi. totalde tüm geceye bakacak olursak ödüllerin çoğunluğunu kadınlar kazandı, buna en prestijli ödül “yılın albümü” dahil. daha ne diyeyim bilmiyorum. güzel mesajlar bunlar. go girls!! #bibanakalmıştıçünkü #ladygaga  #jadapinkettsmith #aliciakeys #michelleobama #jenniferlopez #grammys #grammys2019
name: bibanakalmıştıçünkü

text:
💔💔if valentine’s is really hard for you💔💔on feb 14th i am donating ✨distance reiki✨ to you. ✨✨just **dm me or comment below (don't just like)**to receive distance reiki on feb 14th✨✨ **more detailed instructions below** whether you’re struggling because of loss or loneliness, valentine’s can feel like salt in an open wound for a lot of people. 
no matter how smart, strong and successful you are, i’ve been there and i know much valentine’s can amplify feelings of heartbrokenness.💔 so i’m offering up some time this february 14th during which i will do collective distance reiki for everyone here who is struggling through valentine’s, and wants to receive some support in this way. 💔💔here’s how it’ll work:

1. if you would like to receive some free collective distance reiki on feb 14th, dm me or comment below.

2. in the morning (est) on feb 14th i will do a distance session for everyone who has asked me. i will structure it so that if you comment or message me after i’ve done the session, you will still receive distance reiki on feb 14th.. ‼️if you are in crisis, please seek immediate emergency assistance. if you’re in canada or the us, there are some crisis text numbers below. if you’re anywhere else, please call your local emergency number. ‼️the crisis text line organization provides 24/7, confidential text messaging for people in crisis. a crisis worker will text you back immediately and keep texting with you to help bring you from a hot moment to a calm place.

if you’re in canada: text 686868.

if you’re in the us: text home to 741741.

hold on, breathe deeply, and know that less heavy days can still be yours.

fyi, some additional info on my donation of reiki this week - if you’re not familiar, reiki is love, light and healed information. it goes where it is most needed. i am a reiki master (you can look me up on the cdn reiki assoc. website if you want more info about which style i practice). #valentinesblues #heartbroken #valentinessucks #metoo #trauma #survivor #freereiki #distancereiki #grief #grieving #loss #reiki #lightworker #loveandlight

text_retweet:
reposted from @shesurvived_ -  when i met him over the course of our relationship i saw parts of myself that i valued so much start to slowly disappear. gradually i turned into someone i didn't recognize.

i was always paranoid, nervous and anxious without any explanation. i found myself worrying about if he saw me accidently looking at a guy as i walk, or if he finds out i spoke to a male group member in college. i was too scared to talk, in case i hurt his feelings. i had lost myself and didn't realize until it was too late.
this was one of many attacks.. leading upto it i chose to ignore all the warning signs. clenched fists. punching walls. slamming doors and smashing glasses. truth is i was used to this behavior and i didn't question it like i should have.

that day i remember his temper and paranoia increased as i became non existent. he took my phone in anger to see who'd been texting me, determined to find some kind of evidence of infidelity. he was so adamant in finding something, anything just to have one on me.

he finally returned, convinced i must have deleted all the messages. so he smashed my phone and grabbed me, gripped firmly around my neck, squeezing with all his strength he held onto my throat.
i didn’t know what he was saying when he was screaming at me, i can't even remember what i was thinking. all i remember was the complete and utter shock and terror i felt in my stomach, as i looked into the eyes of someone i loved and felt for a moment that there was a chance that he could have killed me.

i was numb after with him crying, apologising and begging for forgiveness. i never wanted to see him again. i could no longer look him in the eyes. the time he strangled me should have been my wakeup call, but what did i do? 
i forgave him. 
the cycle continued... #abuse#saynotoabuse#domesticviolence#fear#pain#attack#scared#survivor#shesurvived#silent#suffer  #domesticviolence #domesticviolenceawarenessmonth #survivor #domesticviolenceawareness #domesticabuse #awareness #dvam #metoo #dustingoffdomesticviolence #endthestereotype #domesticviolencesurvivor #dvam2018 #purplethursday #breakthesilence #abusesurvivor #narcissisticabuse #believesurvivors #
name: Unbrokenchords

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
et women’s forum: #metoo created empathy, brought change at the workplace
#
the economic times women’s forum 2019 took forward the mission that it launched last year — to collaboratively and urgently build a sustainable culture of empowering india’s half a billion women — through a scintillating day of conversations and debates about encouraging greater participation and reducing gender inequality in every sphere of life, work, and play. the #metoo movement, which has redefined things that were previously considered “normal”, has helped accelerate a cultural change that is happening in the way businesses, and society in general, treat women, but there is scope for further improvement — this was the general view at a panel discussion at the et women’s forum. “#metoo has created an environment of empathy. the biggest positive is that now people don’t dismiss it (harassment faced by women) as rubbish as they did before,” said rekha sharma, chairperson of the national commission for women. “women are talking about it and everybody is listening to them because women are holding each other’s hand.” many organisations have undertaken sensitisation programmes for their employees since october, when the #metoo movement gathered momentum in india, almost a year after taking the world by storm. discourse on gender equality too has come to…

text:
likeability penalty” is a term coined by sheryl sandberg, facebook’s chief operating officer and founder of the lean in foundation. it reflects how women in business are penalised when exhibiting qualities usually attributed to their male counterparts. that is, in a leadership position – one of authority, respect and high achievement – behaviours that are admirable in men, are viewed less favourably in women, or even disliked.
leadership roles require self-assertion, decisiveness, passion, a proactive approach and confidence in one’s skill and ability, which are viewed as positive attributes in male colleagues. however, these qualities tend to be viewed negatively when demonstrated by female leaders.  #gurls #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
you. have to suffer to grow. thats what i believe. i was scared of so many things in my life but know what? i faced them and still do because everything you're running from is simply the truth ☝🏽 i suffered. i've been trough hell. i'd blame everyone and everything around me - my whole life. everyday was about being accepted by others. i wanted them to like me. 
today i know that was a gift. my childhood was a gift. my loneliness was a gift. my insecurity was a gift. the fact that no one helped me was a gift. everything - even when life knocked me down was a gift ☝🏽 when i got called, i fell "asleep" for three days. i'm trying not to think of it but when i do i feel like something forces me to my knees. at this point i realized that a human being is not so human anymore. "we have the ability to go in such a space if you're willing to suffer - and i mean suffer your brain - your body - once they connect you are able to do anything!" that evening - two years ago - changed my whole life. i was on the brick of death. it wasn't about others, it wasn't about my future, about my past, about the shitty people, about anything. it became a personal thing. i came up as a person living "the outside" and found my drive and my strengh by living "the inside" ☝🏽 you have to believe in yourself my love. you have to believe in simply everything.

text:
being an independent woman means you speak your mind. you call people out when they start treating you like shit, even if that means you’ll risk being called crazy or psycho or bitchy. when someone disrespects you, you don’t let them get away with it, because you know what you deserve.
being an independent woman means you support other women. you don’t view them as your competition. you don’t judge them based on what they are wearing or what career they are pursuing. you hand them tampons in bathrooms. you compliment their hair. you help them get home safely. you treat other women as your teammates.
being an independent woman means you never keep toxic people in your world for long. you cut them out as soon as possible, because you know you are strong enough to survive without them. you don’t need their negativity weighing you down. you don’t need to make living more stressful than it already is.
being an independent woman means you are comfortable within the walls of your skin. maybe you step out of the house in sweats or maybe you prefer skintight skirts, but either way, you feel confident wearing them. you love yourself and love your body, because it does so much for you.
even when you are an independent woman, there will still be days when you feel lonely. there will still be times when you wish you were in a relationship because you are sick of the single life. and there is nothing wrong with that.
you can be in a loving relationship and be an independent woman. you can ask for help and be an independent woman. you can feel insecure on certain days and be an independent woman. you can daydream about getting married and having babies and be an independent woman.
your independence doesn’t depend on your relationship status. it depends on your strength. on your energy. on how much you accomplish in a day.

text:
hojt! bussar t/r sthlm c -västerås nu på tors för att backa @jennyorn79 (som åtalas för narkotikabrott efter att blivit drogad och våldtagen av en polis) och protestera mot rättsosäkerheten- har bokat och betalat, du hoppar på och åker med! 
avgång: 8.30 från utanför hotel radisson blu waterfront hotel, nils ericsons plan 4 (se kartan👆) finns plats för 150 pers, om det skulle bli fullt så löser vi annan transport åt övriga. #delfinbuss kör bussarna (tack för snäll rabatt!) hemfärd ca 12.30 (kan bli 13 också beroende på hur allt fortlöper) från västerås central. 
klä dig varmt! vi ska mestadels vara utomhus utanför tingsrätten i västerås. ta gärna med plakat med rimliga budskap. detta är alltså en fredlig men arg aktion. mer praktisk info om själva demonstrationen/aktionen kommer ombord på bussarna. 
media kommer vara på plats, så tänk på att du kan komma att hamna på bild/filmklipp. men vi håller ihop, står samlade och visar hur starkt syster/syskonskapet är💪🔥❤️ kom alltså senast 8.15 nu på torsdag, till utanför waterfront hotel vid sthlm c för att få din plats på buss. upp till kamp!✊ genom att åka med så är du med och skriver historia. #förjenny #metoo

text:
currently in a going through it phase. a lot has been going on around me that i was trying to sweep under the rug, but as everyone knows it’ll always start seeping out. so even though it is the worst timing ever, it is time.
a new anxiety trait has come out of it though, extreme nausea. i’ve often feel sick in my stomach when i’m anxious but this is from my throat if that makes sense? like i’m about to gag. 
i haven’t been able to go to work or class, i’ve been quit paralysed but this. but i have to remember what happened to my friends is a lot in addition to what happened to me. this is a normal reaction! so for the first time i’ve kinda been able to give myself a break about feeling down.

#healing #ptsd #metoo

text_retweet:
#repost @instamariap
・・・
10 reasons why you should have a major #fomo if you haven’t attended #lahootimelo this year? 
1. you’ve majorly missed a great lineup and such impressive talks
2. lahooti made everyone to take something great, back home with them
3. lahooti forced everyone including audience, speakers, critics, thinkers and media to look for solutions for so many burning questions like oppression, fanaticism, education, empowerment, creative expressions, inclusion, tolerance, etc.
4. music was absolutely on point! introducing edm to public is no joke. seeing the audience’s glee and amusement was a thriller in itself
5. gender balanced panels and performances - definitely other festival organisers must learn something from this 
6. if there were only 20% women in the audience on the first day then it became at least 40% on the second day - clearly tells so much more about the atmosphere 
7. there was absolutely no judgementtttt! 
8. audience was madly respectful towards women - raising bars for sindh
9. top-notch security 
10. sindh’s audience deserves a massive shout out for being so well-behaved. they queued up properly to enter the venue. they followed the security protocol for everyone’s safety. this definitely tells so much about sindh’s people

credit for creating and curating such an awesomeness filled weekend goes to @saifsamejo and @sanakhoja. standing ovation.

ps. more pictures and videos will follow in coming posts and stories 
#lahootimelo #lahootimelo2019 #music #edm  #shehzadroy  #dawndotcom #anodetowomen #metoo #ibelieveher #odetowomen

text:
la sessantunesima edizione dei grammy, gli "oscar" dedicati alla musica, si è svolta a los angeles nella notte italiana del 10 febbraio. un’edizione all'insegna del black power e #metoo. la scena è stata dominata da artiste donne e autori/autrici afroamericani a partire dalla presenza a sorpresa di @michelleobama, che nel discorso di apertura ha detto: “la musica mi ha sempre aiutato a raccontare la mia storia. dai dischi di motown che ascoltavo da ragazza a southside chicago, alle canzoni di who run the world che mi hanno dato la carica in questo ultimo decennio. la musica ci aiuta a condividere noi stessi, la nostra dignità e i nostri dolori. le nostre speranze, le nostre gioie. la musica ci mostra che tutto ciò conta” 
l'articolo completo con tutti i nomi dei vincitori su #openonline

text:
"虐待"、"セクハラ"、"me too"。
最近のニュースやsnsでは今まであまり取り上げられてこなかった言葉がよく目にするようになりました。
なぜ今まであまり報道されなかったのか。
それは事件にならなかったり、声を上げられないよう圧力をかけられていたから、そして二次被害にあうから。
.
多くの被害者が泣き寝入りを繰り返している現状。日本ではまだ具体的な研究報告がなく、実態が定かではないそうですが、アメリカでは実際に起こった性犯罪事件の、33.6%ほどしか報告されていないのではと推計されています。性犯罪に対する意識が低い日本ではそれ以下であると言われています。日経dualによると仕事でセクハラにあったことがあると回答した人は56%、そして半数近くが被害を黙っていたそうです。その中でももちろん負けずに声を上げていた方もいます。けれど、「自衛が足りない」など被害者にも落ち度があると責められ、二次被害に遭い、多くの人が声を上げらない、上げられなくなったのが現状です。
本当にその被害者には落ち度はあったのでしょうか。
.
レイプ被害者によく投げられる言葉として「あなたから誘ったんじゃないの？」「露出が高い服装をしていたんだろう」という耳を疑うような言葉をかける人がいます。
海外で行われたレイプ被害者の当時の服装の展示があったのをご存知でしょうか。
被害の時の状況のコメントともにアメリカのカンザス大学で展示が行われました。
tシャツにジーパン、小さな子供用のワンピース。これを見て同じことが言えますか。
そもそも露出が高かったらその気があると判断すること自体が間違っていると私は思います。
.
.
.
毎日snsやニュースで見かける千葉県で起きた虐待死のニュース。見るたび胸が痛くなります。
自身の子を痛めつける動画を撮り、自由を奪い、死に追いやった夫婦。それが傷害罪で逮捕。
おかしいと思いませんか？
なぜ親子だと虐待でまとめられるのでしょう。
どう考えてもそれは殺人ではないでしょうか。その苦しい中でも"助けを求める"という勇気をだし周りの大人に相談しました。
けれどその大人たちは加害者にそのことを伝え、彼女を守ることを怠り、最後には命を落としてしまうという結果となりました。
そして元警察官による集団監禁強姦事件。
「抵抗をやめて大人しくなったから同意したと思った」という加害者の言葉。
抵抗やめると同意の意味になる。
抵抗をし続けたら殺される。
こんな日本で私たちはどうやって生きていったらいいのでしょうか。
.
私も過去に女という性を授かったために、自分という人間であるが故に、様々な被害にあったことがあります。
今もその傷は全く癒えてません。当時の自分に落ち度があったと自分を責め続け、過去の記憶を失ったり、眠れなくなってしまったり、人を信用することが難しくなってしまったり。もう何年も治療を続けていますが、未だにほとんど良くはなっていません。
そして、未だに電車で見知らぬ男性からの嫌がらせや、知人からの心無い発言に涙を流すこともあります。
.
弱者は強者の奴隷ではありません。
子供や女性、お年寄り、力がない人間にこそ寄り添って助け合うのが強さではないのでしょうか。
.
きっとこれを読むあなたも被害者かもしれないし、あなたの周りにも声を上げられないだけで被害にあったことのある方はきっといます。他人事だと思わないでください。
あなたや彼ら、彼女らは、今もその記憶に蓋をして強く生きている方々です。
あなたや、あなたの大切に思う方々が少しでも住みやすい日本になるよう、目を背けず向き合って下さい。
これを読んで少しでも何か考えるきっかけになれれば、嬉しく思います。
これからの日本を作っていくのは今日本に生きる私たちです。少しでも被害にあったあなたや彼ら、彼女らが安心して過ごせるようになりますように。
.
そして心愛ちゃん、どうか安らかにお眠り下さい。
.
.
.
.
.

stem_filter: `` 虐待 `` 、 `` セクハラ `` 、 `` `` 。 最近のニュースやsnsでは今まであまり取り上げられてこなかった言葉がよく目にするようになりました。 なぜ今まであまり報道されなかったのか。 それは事件にならなかったり、声を上げられないよう圧力をかけられていたから、そして二次被害にあうから。 . 多くの被害者が泣き寝入りを繰り返している現状。日本ではまだ具体的な研究報告がなく、実態が定かではないそうですが、アメリカでは実際に起こった性犯罪事件の、33.6 % ほどしか報告されていないのではと推計されています。性犯罪に対する意識が低い日本ではそれ以下であると言われています。日経dualによると仕事でセクハラにあったことがあると回答した人は56 % 、そして半数近くが被害を黙っていたそうです。その中でももちろん負けずに声を上げていた方もいます。けれど、「自衛が足りない」など被害者にも落ち度があると責められ、二次被害に遭い、多くの人が声を上げらない、上げられなくなったのが現状です。 本当にその被害者には落ち度はあったのでしょうか。 . レイプ被害者によく投げられる言葉として「あなたから誘ったんじゃないの？」「露出が高い服装をしていたんだろう」という耳を疑うような言葉をかける人がいます。 海外で行われたレイプ被害者の当時の服装の展示があったのをご存知でしょうか。 被害の時の状況のコメントともにアメリカのカンザス大学で展示が行われました。 tシャツにジーパン、小さな子供用のワンピース。これを見て同じことが言えますか。 そもそも露出が高かったらその気があると判断すること自体が間違っていると私は思います。 . . . 毎日snsやニュースで見かける千葉県で起きた虐待死のニュース。見るたび胸が痛くなります。 自身の子を痛めつける動画を撮り、自由を奪い、死に追いやった夫婦。それが傷害罪で逮捕。 おかしいと思いませんか？ なぜ親子だと虐待でまとめられるのでしょう。 どう考えてもそれは殺人ではないでしょうか。その苦しい中でも `` 助けを求める `` という勇気をだし周りの大人に相談しました。 けれどその大人たちは加害者にそのことを伝え、彼女を守ることを怠り、最後には命を落としてしまうという結果となりました。 そして元警察官による集団監禁強姦事件。 「抵抗をやめて大人しくなったから同意したと思った」という加害者の言葉。 抵抗やめると同意の意味になる。 抵抗をし続けたら殺される。 こんな日本で私たちはどうやって生きていったらいいのでしょうか。 . 私も過去に女という性を授かったために、自分という人間であるが故に、様々な被害にあったことがあります。 今もその傷は全く癒えてません。当時の自分に落ち度があったと自分を責め続け、過去の記憶を失ったり、眠れなくなってしまったり、人を信用することが難しくなってしまったり。もう何年も治療を続けていますが、未だにほとんど良くはなっていません。 そして、未だに電車で見知らぬ男性からの嫌がらせや、知人からの心無い発言に涙を流すこともあります。 . 弱者は強者の奴隷ではありません。 子供や女性、お年寄り、力がない人間にこそ寄り添って助け合うのが強さではないのでしょうか。 . きっとこれを読むあなたも被害者かもしれないし、あなたの周りにも声を上げられないだけで被害にあったことのある方はきっといます。他人事だと思わないでください。 あなたや彼ら、彼女らは、今もその記憶に蓋をして強く生きている方々です。 あなたや、あなたの大切に思う方々が少しでも住みやすい日本になるよう、目を背けず向き合って下さい。 これを読んで少しでも何か考えるきっかけになれれば、嬉しく思います。 これからの日本を作っていくのは今日本に生きる私たちです。少しでも被害にあったあなたや彼ら、彼女らが安心して過ごせるようになりますように。 . そして心愛ちゃん、どうか安らかにお眠り下さい。 . . . . .

text:
~ "guardian angel"  a poem
·
violated by the hands of a sexual deviant
·
those eyes...good to evil in mere seconds
· 
sleepless nights merge seamlessly into restless days
·
each one blending into the next, without fail
·
what day is it?
·
i see his face when i close my eyes
·
how long until that goes away? 
never?
·
going anywhere alone is out of the question...but for how long?
·
too many friends to count, i'm always there for them
·
i'm here...struggling. where are they?
·
why am i here, suffering...alone with my horrified thoughts?
·
the late afternoon sun beaming radiantly through the blinds
·
my sleepy eyes staring at the wall as if in a trance
·
shapes of light slowly evolving as the sun declines
·
a ghostly figure appears before my eyes
·
my guardian angel, perhaps?
·
is this all i need to watch over me?
·
no...
·
·
~ © addie.g.poetry. november 11, 2018, 6:45 pm.
·
~ © addison g. photography. november 11, 2018 6:25 pm.
·

die intention der woche lautet: ich blicke liebevoll auf mich selbst ✨ #realiseyourinnerglow

kannst du dich noch an das posting vom 11. november 2018 erinnern ⁉️
👋 hier ging es um die klopfakupressur (eft) und darum drei probleme wegzukopfen z.b. antriebslosigkeit, übergewicht, auftrittsangst usw.
👀 diese woche wollen wir genauer hinsehen! was steckt hinter diesen themen? 🌳 ein beispiel: übergewicht ist das symptom (=blatt) und dahinter liegt die emotion (=ast) "ich schäme mich dick zu sein". das ereignis eine schicht tiefer lautet (=stamm) "in der schule wurde ich immer gemobbt, weil ich dick war.". ⛔️ was ist der limitierende glaubenssatz (=wurzel), der dich seither bremst? ich bin nicht liebenswert. ich bin hässlich...?! bearbeite diesen glaubenssatz mit der eft methode
